title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients very well.
Place in a casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Place this on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Beat 3 eggs until frothy. Add sugar, oil and vanilla to eggs and beat until thick and lemon-colored.
Add flour mixture and mix.
Stir in squash.
Fold in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: super chicken nuggets
directions: You will need 3 small flat-bottomed bowls or pans.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips on top before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Spread cooked noodles in greased 9-inch square or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Blend remaining ingredients in food processor or blender. Pour over noodles.
Top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: mamma dee's corn bread mush
directions: Start water to boiling.
Add salt, sugar, oil and green onion. Cook 15 minutes.
Lower to medium heat.
Stir in cornmeal (like cooking grits); stir until mixture becomes stiff and thick in texture.
Remove mixture to wax paper for 5 minutes.
Hand pat into desired shape.
Fill Fry Daddy to oil level; heat oil until hot.
Drop in 4 to 6 bread pods.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Bread is ready when it becomes golden brown and floats to top of oil. Yields 16 to 20 pieces.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef; drain if necessary.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sheet cake brownies
directions: Bring to boil water, oleo and cocoa.
Pour over flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in large cookie sheet (with sides) that has been greased and floured.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Ice as soon as removed from oven.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: In ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, mix flour, nuts, brown sugar and margarine.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Save 1/2 cup baked crumbs for topping.
In large bowl, combine egg whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed until stiff, about 10 minutes.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over crust and top with crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.

title: wilted cole slaw
directions: Place vegetables in large jar.
Add oil and seasonings.
In saucepan, bring sugar and vinegar to a boil; pour over vegetables. Cover jar and refrigerate.
This will keep up to a month in refrigerator.

title: hot rolls or cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In mixer, beat until well mixed.
Let rise in bowl.
Put on lightly floured board.
Knead several minutes.
Put into 2 loaves, 18 hot rolls or roll thin. Spread oleo on top, then sugar and cinnamon.
Roll into log; cut into 22 pieces.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, sausages (remove from casings), green onions, garlic, crumbs, eggs, tomato paste, thyme, salt, pepper and wine. Mix thoroughly.
Place half the mixture in a loaf pan.
Make a well down the center and fill with cheese.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit the soda and salt.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (cake mix and pudding) into bowl.
Add oil, sour cream, eggs and water; mix with water and chocolate chips.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sharon's steak and peppers
directions: Brown round steak in oil.
Add green peppers and onions and cook until tender.
Blend gravy mix and water and pour over meat, peppers and onions.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: beet and onion salad
directions: Bring to a boil the vinegar, water, mustard and sugar.
Pour warm dressing over beets and onion.
Chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing with onion, tomato, green pepper, olives and cheese. Cook pasta and add. Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use fresh, firm, small cucumbers.
Wash and cut them into sticks.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers and let them stand overnight.
The next morning, pack into clean jars.
Make a solution of ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling hot over the cucumbers in jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini or squash with onion in water until tender.
Do not peel unless large.
Drain well in colander.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Add all of the ingredients. Pour over squash and mix.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until done. Set aside.

title: white chili
directions: Saute the chicken breasts cut in bite size pieces (or ground meat) in 1 tablespoon oil.
Do not brown. Add all the remaining ingredients except white kidney beans. When chicken and onion are cooked, add white kidney beans.
Heat until serving temperature. Garnish with grated Monterey Jack cheese, 1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro, sour cream and chopped fresh tomatoes.
If you prefer hot chili, you may add 1 minced jalapeno or more cayenne.

title: golden noodles and sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° approximately 40 minutes.

title: pork steaks and rice
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Add soup, water, rice and mushrooms.
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes, adding more water or tomato juice if needed, until steaks are tender.

title: braised beef in beer
directions: Pound steak in flour and salt.
Brown in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Thicken slightly with 1 tablespoon flour in 2 tablespoons water.
Serve immediately.
Can be prepared ahead and can be frozen.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, combine Crisco, oleo, cocoa and water and bring to a boil.
Gradually add this to flour and sugar, stirring constantly.
Put soda in buttermilk and add unbeaten eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla. Pour into 11 x 14-inch pan and bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-kiwi salad with basil
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add kiwi fruit and strawberries.
Toss well.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Stir in basil just before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tuna fish, soups, milk, soy sauce, half of noodles and nuts.
Put in greased or sprayed 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Cover with remaining noodles and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes; add mayonnaise, cheese and seasonings.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: oven baked smelts
directions: Mix egg, cold water and salt together.
Dip cleaned smelts in egg mixture, then roll in dry bread crumbs or flour.
Place in a well-greased pan and drop a little oil on top.
Bake in 450° preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Turning is unnecessary.

title: country squash
directions: In thick skillet, heat oil and add potatoes and onions.
Slice squash over the top and add garlic.
Season with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Stir, turn heat to low and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: porcupines in mushroom sauce
directions: Combine uncooked rice with ground meat, onion, green pepper, celery, egg, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine mushroom soup mix with water and heat to boiling.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover tightly and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove and stir in sour cream.
Serves 6 generously.

title: banana muffins(also suitable for diabetic food plans.)
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, cereal, sugar and baking powder.
In a smaller bowl, beat egg slightly.
Beat in bananas, milk and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened, but lumpy. Spoon batter into 12 paper lined cups, filling them half full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Yields 12.
Serving size: 1.

title: africa-bobotie
directions: Before you start, set the oven to 350°.
Cut the crusts off the bread and break it into chunks.
Soak it in half of the milk. Chop the onion.
Heat the oil in a pan and fry the onion over a low heat for 10 minutes.
Add the beef, curry powder, lemon juice, nuts, raisins, salt and pepper to pan.
Fry until the meat is brown all over.
Spoon all of it into an ovenproof dish.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: In ungreased 2 quart round microproof dish, mix bread and raisins. Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended. In 4 cup glass measure,heat milk and butter on HI setting 4 1/2 to 5 minutes, or until steaming hot.

Gradually stir in egg mixture. Pour over bread and raisins, sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover with waxed paper. Cook on simmer or lower setting 12 to 15 minutes. When cooked, center may be slightly soft but will set as pudding cools.
Serve warm or chilled.
Not only is this a good and tasty dessert, but an economical way to use up old or dry bread. For an interesting and different taste mix in a teaspoon of grated orange or lemon rind.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to boil first five ingredients, set aside.
Mix in large bowl, corn, peas, and beans that have been drained.
Add chopped onion, pepper, celery, and the pimiento.
Pour liquid over vegetables.
Mix well refrigerate awhile, until flavors mix.

title: bill's grouper fingers
directions: In shallow bowl, mix eggs and sherry together.
Dip fingers in bowl until covered.
Remove from bowl and cover with bread crumbs. Melt butter in frypan and add fingers; fry until golden brown, occasionally spooning melted butter over fingers.
Best served with home fries and cole slaw.

title: captain don's dream-of-the-sea sauce
directions: Add ingredients.
Heat until boiling, then simmer over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve over rotini pasta or shells.

title: creamy pineapple pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Pour the crushed pineapple into the pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mix and vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda in bowl.
Melt 2 sticks oleo, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup milk and bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: johnnie's venison chili
directions: Combine meat, onions and garlic.
Brown in Dutch oven in oil. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Simmer, covered, 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients; dress with vinaigrette.
Whisk together mustard and vinegar; slowly whisk in oil and seasonings.
Gently toss pasta to coat, use additional dressing to refresh salad as needed.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into short sticks or small balls. Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach quickie
directions: Place peach halves in shallow baking dish.
Put a dab of butter on each one.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on each one. Drizzle with honey and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Broil for 5 minutes (graham crackers will look slightly brown).
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: shell salad
directions: Toss together and let stand overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix well and add broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until set.
Remove from oven and top with onion rings or potato chips.
Return to oven and bake until top browns.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Heat
oven

Mix

sugar, water and eggs in large bowl until smooth.

Do not overbake.
Run

while warm to loosen sides. Cool

if desired, or sprinkle with powdered sugar).
Cut into bars.

title: spice bundt cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs, slightly beaten.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk slowly.
Add flavorings and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip well and spread over first mixture.
Mix pudding with milk; spread on second mixture.
Top with the remaining half of the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave harvard beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into measuring cup so it measures 2/3 cup (add water if necessary).
Set aside.
Mix together cornstarch and sugar in a deep 1 1/2-quart nonmetallic casserole.
Gradually add beet liquid and vinegar to cornstarch mixture and stir until smooth.
Heat covered on Full power, 1 1/2 minutes or until it comes to a boil.
Stir.
Boil liquid for an additional minute. Stir after 30 seconds.
Add beets and heat uncovered on Full power for 3 minutes.

title: greek lemon chicken soup
directions: Bring broth, celery, carrots and onion to boil in large pot. Add rice to soup and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add chicken to soup and simmer until cooked through, about 10 minutes. Beat eggs and lemon juice in small bowl until blended.
Gradually add egg mixture to soup stirring constantly until mixture forms ribbons, about 3 minutes.
Season soup to taste with salt and pepper.

title: easy western tamale casserole
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Drain tamales, reserving liquid, and cut in half-inch slices.
Grease 2-quart baking dish and line with tamale slices.

title: peach crisp(shirley knapp)
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a bowl.
Cut butter into oats mixture; use pastry blender (coarse).
Stir in pecans.
Spoon peaches into greased 9
x 13-inch pan.
Lightly crumble mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Put ice cream on top.

title: party mix
directions: Melt oleo and garlic salt to taste.
Put dry ingredients in pan and pour oleo over.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender (20 to 30 minutes).
Cool and grate fine.
Heat 1/4 cup butter with the soup in a saucepan. Blend in the sour cream, green onion and cheese.
Stir in the grated potatoes.
Blend well and transfer to a buttered casserole. Top with crushed cornflakes and tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made ahead and frozen.

title: mama's butter crackers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add yolks, then flour.
Beat whites until stiff and fold in carefully.
Spread very, very thinly and evenly on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Watch carefully for burning.
Cut immediately into squares.

title: irish coffee pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell. Refrigerate.
May garnish top with whipped cream and chocolate.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fold in cream. Serve cold.

title: boiled cookies or no bake
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa
1 1/2 minutes at hard boil, then remove from heat.
Add your oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla, then spoon out on wax paper and cool.
Kids love them.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook beef until lightly browned (not hard).
Drain off grease. Combine all ingredients in slow electric cooker.
Cook 10 to 12 hours on low or 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Add salt to vegetable mixture and mix well.
Let stand for 4 hours; drain well.
Add sugar, vinegar, water and spices to vegetables.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix milk and sugar; bring to a boil.
Beat eggs well; pour hot milk over eggs.
Pour into preheated crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini fans with herb butter
directions: In a small bowl, toss the bread crumbs with the Parmesan.
In another small bowl, cream together the butter, tarragon and parsley with salt and pepper to taste.
Keeping attached at one end, cut the zucchini lengthwise into four 1/4-inch thick slices.
Spread some of the herb butter carefully between the layers and press the slices together lightly.
Separate the slices slightly to form a fan and bake the fans with 1/4 cup water in a buttered baking pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inches, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle the fans with the bread crumb mixture and broil them under the broiler about 4 inches from the heat until golden.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Thaw dough according to package.
Place dough in bowl and cover with a little oil.
Cover bowl with a light towel and let rise in warm place for about 4 hours.
Roll dough out.

Layer Provolone and pepperoni, then roll up tight like a jelly roll. Place seam side down on ungreased cookie sheet and tuck in ends. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until light brown on top. Let cool and slice into 1-inch sections.
Other tried and true combos:

title: kosher potato salad
directions: Boil and skin potatoes.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Pour hot liquid which has just come to boil for potatoes.
Refrigerate. Do not use before 2 to 3 hours.

title: jill's shrimp and pasta for 2
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook garlic but do not brown.
Stir in tomatoes and cook for 1 minute.
Add seasonings and cook for 5 minutes.
Add Sambuco, cook for 5 minutes.
In another pan, heat the rest of the oil.
Lightly salt and pepper shrimp and cook until just pink.
In 9 x 12-inch pan, layer shrimp, pepper flakes and tomato mixture.
Cover and chill until time for dinner.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle before baking with cheese.
Serve over rigatoni.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Let boil 1 minute; remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melts; pour over cornflakes and spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda, in a heavy skillet.
Stir until completely melted.
Add soda and stir.
Mixture will be puffy.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Don't use spoon. Smooth by turning pan.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: snicker brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine caramels and 2/3 cup evaporated milk; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until candy has melted; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine 2/3 cup evaporated milk, cake mix, melted butter and chopped nuts.
Press 1/2 of the mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture and crumble remaining dough on top. Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: berry crisp
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine oats, brown sugar, flour and salt. Cut in butter until mixture is like coarse crumbs. Place berries in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: lumpia
directions: Wash
vegetables;
slice finely.
Wash shrimp; take off shell and head.
Cut shrimp onto 1/2-inch pieces.
Slice onion finely. Saute
pork
in
2	teaspoons of oil and garlic.
Add shrimp; cook
until reddish.
Add sliced vegetables and mongo sprout.
Add salt
and	ajinomoto to taste.
Cook with medium heat
to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; drain and cool thoroughly.
Place
1 tablespoon	of
meat mixture in each lumpia wrapper;
fold	into envelope style, sealing ends with water. Deep
fry	each
lumpia in	oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.	Best when served hot.

title: amy's lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Use large cup.
Beat eggs until foamy; set aside.
Combine sugar, butter and Crisco; blend until creamy. Add flavor and coloring.
Add 1 cup flour and blend with egg each time.
Mix well.
Grease large pound cake pan; dust excess flour from pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool before icing.

title: 30 minute dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Let rise.
Do not punch down, just roll and use.

title: spaghetti or pizza sauce
directions: Blend onions and mangoes in blender and drain.
Cook juice, onions, mangoes and hot pepper for 1 hour.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 1 more hour.
Put in jars and seal.
Cold pack for 20 minutes or pressure for 5 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Makes 7 quarts.
(Use less salt and sugar and taste. Also, watch for boil over.)

title: perfect-every-time-fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, salt, butter and marshmallow cream in a large bowl.
Reserve.
Combine evaporated milk and sugar in a large saucepan; place over moderate heat.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 13 minutes.
If you are using a candy thermometer, the temperature of the sugar mixture should register 236°.
Pour hot milk/sugar over chocolate mixture and beat with a spoon until chocolate is melted and blended.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread into 2 greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans and refrigerate until candy is firm.
Cut into small squares.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: meat balls and cabbage
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Make into meat balls and brown.
Layer the cabbage, onion, rice and browned meat balls. Top with the soup and milk.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in unsalted water.
Remove from bones and set aside, reserving broth.
Stir melted margarine into dressing.
In greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place layer of dressing crumbs, a layer of chicken and a layer of celery soup, diluted with a can of chicken broth.
Repeat layers, using chicken soup, diluted with a can of broth.
Top with layer of dressing crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Put corn flakes on top and pour the 1/4 cup butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Add first 5 ingredients together in mixing bowl and beat 5 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan, approximately 12 x 9 x 2-inches, and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
When cake is baked, remove from oven and prick top of cake with a fork.
Pour over the cake powdered sugar and lemon juice which have been mixed together.

title: old fashion egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk and beat well.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Put in a deep pie pan and cook at 350° until done.

title: lace cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add oatmeal and flour.
Add all ingredients and blend well.
Spoon mixture for desired size on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, oil and sour cream. Stir in cornmeal, green pepper, onion, pimento and chilies. Mix well. Pour half of cornmeal mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with beef. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese. Spoon remaining cornmeal mixture over cheese. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is done. Serves 10.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill at least two hours before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, then add remaining ingredients. Use bread pan; cook for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Peel and chop onion.
Clean and slice mushrooms.
Heat butter in skillet.
Brown meat quickly. Reduce heat; add onion and mushrooms.
Saute for a few minutes. Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add tomato paste or puree and mustard.
Stir in whipping cream; cook, covered, on low heat for about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream. Heat, but do not cook over high heat.
The sour cream may curdle. Serve.
Good served with steamed rice and string beans.

title: tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, mustard, Miracle Whip, relish, salt, pepper and olives to a creamy consistency or to your taste.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Cook macaroni for 6 to 8 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix sausage, sauce, shredded cheeses and macaroni.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or large casserole dish.
Sprinkle a little grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot all the way through.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: skillet steak
directions: Place the steak in a large iron skillet.
Rub Worcestershire into steak.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with vegetables. Mix lemon juice and tomato sauce together and pour over top.

title: phyllis' mexican casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan and place corn chips on bottom. Mix together and heat the ground beef, pinto beans, soup, tomato sauce, picante sauce and water. Add chili powder, garlic powder, salt, pepper and onion or onion flakes to taste. Pour over chips. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender. In a large bowl, mix soup, salt, pepper and cheese. Add onions. Add drained carrots. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 or 8 x 12 baking dish. Melt remaining butter. Add croutons; mix and sprinkle over carrots. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: saucepan cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes; remove from heat, add vanilla, mix and then add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper lined cookie sheet and chill until set.

title: picante sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Chop onions and peppers.
Add spices and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and hot bath for 10 minutes.

title: ranch party mix
directions: Mix oil and dip in a big bowl and add box of oyster crackers. Toss and cover with wax paper overnight.
Stir in 1/2 bag of pretzels, M&M's and peanuts.

title: fiesta chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Pour 1 can enchilada sauce in 9x13 baking dish.
In lg. bowl, combine chicken, sour cream, chilies, onions, and salt.
Stir in 1 c. cheese.
Spoon about 1/3 c. chicken mix. down center of tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in prepared dish.
Pour remaining can of enchilada sauce over top,
sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered for 30 min. or until cheese is melted and enchiladas are heated through.

title: spicy doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light.
Beat in milk and melted shortening.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat into the mixture until smooth and well blended.
Chill for several hours.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to 3/8-inch thickness.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Fry in deep hot shortening; turn once, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in paper bag.
Shake doughnuts in cinnamon mix.

title: old fashion egg noodles
directions: Put flour and salt in a bowl.
Make a well in center of the flour and put eggs and water in the well.
Work the flour into the eggs to create a pie dough mixture.
Roll it out as thin as possible, then sprinkle top with flour.
Roll dough up like a jelly roll and slice very thin to make the noodles.
Keep flour on the noodles to prevent sticking together.
Have 3 quarts chicken or beef broth at a rolling boil.
Add the noodles, a few at a time. When all are in, cook 20 minutes and serve.

title: potato carrot casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, cook potatoes and carrots, covered, in boiling water for 12 minutes.
Drain.
Cook bacon; drain, crumble and set aside.
In mixer, mash potatoes and carrots with potato masher.
Beat in milk until creamy.
Stir in eggs, 1/2 cup cheese, onion and sour cream.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 minutes; sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In a bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter; press evenly onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix shortening and next 3 ingredients until creamy.
Mix in pineapple, then flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon, 2-inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cookies with nutmeg and 1 tablespoon sugar, combined.
Bake until golden, about 12 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: herb chicken
directions: In a bowl combine all ingredients (except chicken).
You may wish to add water to thin ingredients.
Wash chicken and dry thoroughly, inside and out.
Beginning with the neck opening, slip fingers between skin and flesh and loosen the skin on one side of the breast.
Now loosen the other side.
Insert the combined ingredients into this cavity.
Rub the outside of the chicken with those ingredients and place the remaining in the chicken cavity. Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken on rack or roasting pan uncovered for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Baste chicken and cover.
Baste chicken every 15 minutes or until juices run clear when the thickest part of the thigh is pierced.
Approximately 1 1/2 hours (20 minutes per pound) total cooking time.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In large pot, combine water, chicken broth, soup, chicken, onion, carrots, vermouth, garlic, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil and add tortellini.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add broccoli and simmer for an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Serve with cheese.
Serves 10.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix with sweet salad dressing.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Add green beans and corn.
Mix soup, cheese, onion and sour cream.
Pour over beans and corn.
Add Ritz crackers over top of casserole.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake 30 minutes or 35 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grind cheese; mix with butter and stir well.
Add flour and red pepper.
Make into a roll and put in cookie press.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, flour, salt and lemon rind in saucepan.
Add apples, margarine and lemon juice; cook over low heat until apples are partly done.
Spoon apple mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fast 'n easy chili
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes. Makes about 6 servings.

title: chicken garden skillet
directions: In electric skillet, melt shortening. Meanwhile, dredge chicken pieces in seasoned flour. Brown slowly in the hot shortening about 10 minutes, turning once.
Reduce heat.
Add chicken broth and sherry. Cover and cook for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: ann's fruit cobbler pie
directions: * Buttermilk can be made with 1 cup milk and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Let stand or use the real thing.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, crisco, brown sugar, milk, and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add egg, beat until blended. Combine flour, salt, and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix just until blended. Add chocolate chips. Drop by heaping teaspoon, 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 7-8 min.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container. Use 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sour cream; mix in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with bite sized pieces of Hawaiian bread or chips.

title: coconut pie best
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350°, or until golden brown.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a microwavable dish.
Put in microwave oven on High for two minutes and stir.
(Stir very quickly with spoon, sprayed with nonstick coating, because it will harden very quickly.)

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine cheese, margarine and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt. Beat in eggs (one at a time), beating well after each addition.
Add cake flour until well blended. Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and mushrooms in a zesty tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in a 6-quart casserole or Dutch oven over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add chicken and brown for 6 minutes on each side.
Transfer chicken to a plate.
Add onion, garlic, peppers and mushrooms to casserole and saute, stirring often, for 10 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, salt and red pepper (cayenne), then add the browned chicken.
Spoon the sauce over the chicken and sprinkle with the salami.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in pasta or orzo and water.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is tender and the chicken is no longer pink on the inside (about 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with the parsley.
Serves 4.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix the night before and refrigerate. Good as a topping for other desserts. Use for dipping sliced bananas, strawberries, oranges, melon, etc.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as listed.
Make ahead of time. Refrigerate until served.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Measure flour, salt and soda together.
Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add flour mixture and drained mandarin oranges. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While still hot, punch holes in cake and pour over cake a mixture of the last 3 ingredients which you have cooked 3 minutes only.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and walnuts.
Fold in whipping cream and pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf
pan. Freeze firm, about 6 hours or overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put everything in a bowl.
Mix well.
Mold into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, butter flavoring and buttermilk.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Add chili powder, salt, ketchup and mustard.
Stir; add water.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter; stir in vanilla.
Pour over mixed sugar, cocoa and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan (dish).
Cut when set.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Cream the cheese with a fork until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend well with mixer.
Add onions and 1/2 of each pepper.
Mix with spoon.
Roll into ball and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.
You may garnish with remaining peppers if desired.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Boil corn syrup and sugar for 5 seconds.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well, and pour over popped popcorn.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add flour, milk, egg yolks, salt and pepper, one ingredient at a time until blended.
Remove from heat.
Place crab meat in a lightly greased glass baking dish, 9 x 9-inch.
Pour sauce over crab and sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: grape hull pie
directions: Boil hulls until tender.
Take hulls out of juice and sugar until sweet.
Add 1/4 cup of flour, egg yolks, milk and margarine. Cook until thick, then pour in pie shell (unbaked).
Use egg whites to make meringue.
Beat egg whites until they peak; sweeten to taste.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover with enough water to cook shrimp. Cook until shrimp is firm.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast drop scones
directions: Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Add raisins and milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out into a bowl, reserving shell.
Beat potato, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and parsley until well blended. Stir in tomato.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Add scalded milk and cook over low heat until the mixture thickens.
Beat egg yolks and pour part of milk mixture over them.
Then pour back into pan. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue from 3 egg whites.

title: mud butte jerkey
directions: Chill steak and slice in very thin strips.
Cut with grain.

title: chocolate surprise cookies
directions: Beat butter at med. speed until creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, cocoa, and soda.
Add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and 1/2 c. chopped pecans.
Cover dough and refrigerate 1 hour.
Combine remaining 1/2 c. pecans and 1 Tbsp. sugar.
Set aside. Gently press 1 Tbsp. cookie dough around each caramel candy forming a ball.
Dip 1 side of cookie in pecan mixture.
Place pecan side up 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
(Cookies will look soft.)
Let cool 1 min. on baking sheets before removing them.

title: fudge pecan ice cream sundae pie
directions: Crush cookies and add butter.
Press mixture into a 9-inch pie tin (forms crust).
Press in 1/2 of the ice cream.
Place over it 1/2 of the sauce and 1 cup of pecans.
Layer remaining ice cream, sauce and pecans.
Cover tightly and freeze 12 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake chocolate cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on mix.
While hot, pierce cake all over and pour 1/2 cup Kahlua over cake.
Cool and cut into thirds.
Prepare mousse according to directions on package (or make your own).
In a large glass bowl, make three layers: cake, mousse and topping.
Sprinkle candy (ground) over topping.

title: never fail peanut brittle(makes you want to dance!)
directions: Put the salt, soda and butter in a small dish ready in dump in later. Boil sugar, Karo and water until thread spins (268° is better) then add peanuts and stir continuously after peanuts are added. Cook until it turns a brownish gold (298° is safer) on medium-high heat. Take from heat and add butter, salt and soda. Stir until well mixed. Pour into 4 foil-lined and buttered pie plates to cool. When cold, break into pieces and store in cookie cans!

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water (Minute rice works well also).
Set aside.
Cook onions and green peppers in oleo for approximately 2 minutes.
Add corn and cook for a few minutes.
Melt Velveeta in milk in saucepan.
Add rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cornish hens with rosemary mustard sauce
directions: Rub the hens with oil and place on a roasting rack.
Mix together the next 5 ingredients in a bowl, whisking until well blended.
Brush the sauce over the hens and place 2 sprigs of rosemary into each cavity.

title: meatballs in mushroom gravy
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Roll beef into balls and brown. Then mix mushroom soup and water; pour over balls.
Simmer over low heat 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, using electric mixer until smooth. Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix the flour, 1 cup
sugar, salt, cocoa powder and baking soda in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Blend water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; pour into well and whisk until smooth.
Spoon batter into cupcake tins.
Beat cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and egg in medium bowl.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Spoon over batter.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes. Remove from tins to cool.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Put all in same bowl in any order.
Fill cupcake cup 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 24.
Keeps very well.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Melt oleo and mix in garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheets.
Serve warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Knead until smooth, roll into 1-inch thickness.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Butter top.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Place in covered dish and pour tomatoes over top.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook 4 hours or more at 275°.
Do not open while cooking.

title: pepperoni and potatoes
directions: Slice peeled potatoes thin in food processor.
Fry in covered skillet with as little amount of oil as possible.
When potatoes are all brown and crispy, remove from burner and add 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Cover with 1/2 package of pepperoni and 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese.
Pour other half of tomato sauce on top and rest of pepperoni.
Top with remainder of cheese.

title: french toast
directions: Beat
eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
When well mixed, add milk and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Put butter in skillet.
Dip bread slices
in
mixture; coat both sides.
Fry each side of bread until
golden
brown.
Serve
hot
with syrup, honey or preserves.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Add cream of tartar and beat until forms stiff peaks. Add sugar gradually and beat well; add pecans and vanilla. Fold in crushed crackers. Pour into slightly buttered pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. When the pie is cooled, top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: To make crust, mix together margarine, pecan pieces and flour with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Spread onto a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan squares
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar; beat with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs, beating well. Add vanilla and mix in. Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to sugar mixture and mix well. Stir in pecans. Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle immediately with powdered sugar. Let cool completely and cut into squares.

title: espresso brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a square baking pan (9-inch).
Stir first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Whisk in sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, then the bittersweet chocolate.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: very berry cheesecake
directions: Use a graham cracker crust for a large pie dish.

title: pork chops and rice dressing
directions: Fry pork chops until brown on both sides.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until onions are soft.
Add water and let come to a boil.
Add green onions, pimentos and uncooked rice. Lower heat and simmer for about 30 minutes with the lid on until the rice is done.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together. Start with 4 drops of flavoring, and then carefully add flavoring and color as desired. Knead until pie dough consistency is achieved. Add sugar to make softer or decrease sugar for a firmer consistency. Take small pinch and roll into a ball in granulated sugar. Press into mold; remove excess and unmold at once onto waxed paper.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Melt butter and saute onion and celery.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Put sage and almonds in dressing (stuffing).
Pour butter, water and vegetable combination into dressing and mix until all is moist (more hot water may be used).
Butter flounder liberally and salt and pepper both sides.
Place dressing in center of flounder. With toothpicks, pin tail to upper part of flounder (above dressing).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Melt butter in pan over low heat.
While melting, mix sugar and eggs.
Stir in butter; mix well.
Stir in cocoa, flour and nuts.
Bake in oblong cake pan.
Butter sides and bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Chill and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice.
Boil potato slices until done and drain.
Melt butter.
Chop up a little onion and put with butter. Add 2 teaspoons flour to mixture and mix well and bring to a good warm.
Add salt and pepper.
Add about 1 cup of milk and bring slowly to a boil.
When mixture begins to thicken, pour over potatoes in Pyrex dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: heath sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, egg, soda and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in Heath bits.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are very lightly browned.

title: raisin-carrot muffins
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add dry ingredients and blend.
Fold in the carrots, raisins, walnuts and pineapple.
Pour into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars and cream thoroughly.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour and soda together; work into creamed mixture.
Form into balls and flatten out on a baking sheet with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Fold aluminum foil to form a ring in the bottom of the crock-pot.
Place roast meat side down.
Chop onion and carrots. Place on top of roast.
Mix gravy with water.
Pour over roast and veggies.
If frozen place on high for 1 1/2 hours, then low for 6 hours.
If thawed, cook 8 to 10 hours.
Goes good with homemade noodles.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Place half of potatoes in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Layer remaining ingredients on top of the potatoes.
Season as you go.
Place second half of potatoes on top and some stewed tomatoes or spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Chill; serve on shrimp, crab meat or other seafoods.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat into eggs until light and fluffy.
Add cooking oil and vanilla.
Stir flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together; add to first mixture.
Add grated zucchini, nutmeats and raisins or dates.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: 1918 doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out and cut with a round cookie cutter.
Use thimble to cut hole in center.
Melt some lard in a pan, add doughnuts.
Cook on one side, then turn and cook on other side.
Roll in sugar or powdered sugar.

title: ham-bone soup
directions: Take 1 pkg. each:
kidney beans, lentils, black-eyed peas, Great Northern beans, split peas, pinto beans, navy and white lima beans, butter beans and barley.
Store in closed container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in large casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Place into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Top with whole, drained cherries. Chill for 3 hours or overnight before serving.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda and salt in large bowl.
Bring to boil margarine, cocoa, oil and water.
Pour mixture over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and mix well. (Don't use electric mixer.)
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Cook at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: hibachi shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add shrimp; marinate for at least 1 hour.
Cook on hibachi.
May be broiled in oven or cooked on stove.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Bake brownies as directed on package and let cool.
Mix mousse as directed, but do not chill.
Crush candy bars into fine pieces.
Crumble brownies.

title: breakfast casserole(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Crumble sausage and fry; drain off grease. Beat eggs. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix sausage, eggs and cheese; pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *One 16 ounce bag frozen vegetable combination of broccoli, cauliflower and carrots, cooked and drained and 1 can sliced potatoes, drained.

title: jack pots
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Place each biscuit into an ungreased muffin cup.
Spoon meat mixture over biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: kielbasa with red cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, orange peel, garlic, salt, nutmeg, pepper and cloves.
In a Dutch oven, arrange in layers half of cabbage, half of onions and half of apples.
Sprinkle with half of brown sugar mixture.
Top with half of pepper strips and repeat.
Pour orange juice and vinegar over top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour.
Add
sugar and spices, then mix in oil and other ingredients.
Preheat
oven
to
Cook for 30 minutes, then lower
heat to 375° for about 30 minutes more. Use greased tube pan.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place broccoli in a medium pot and cook in boiling water for about 12 minutes.
After cooking, drain off all water and let cool thoroughly.
Cut into small pieces.
Use only the full, dark green, rosette part of the broccoli and the tender part of the stems.
Place cut pieces in a medium bowl and set aside.

title: baked fish
directions: Wash fish, add salt and pepper and rub with lemon juice.
Saute onion, add tomatoes, garlic and celery.
Simmer.
Blend well.
Add potatoes and simmer for 10 minutes more.
Lightly oil baking pan. Place fish in pan and pour tomato-potato mixture over fish.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: london broil
directions: Score both sides of the steak in a diamond pattern, about 1/8-inch deep.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Take biscuits and dip in butter, then coat with cinnamon and sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican spice cake
directions: Put ingredients into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Drain fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough 7-Up to fruit juice to make 3 cups of liquid.
Add fruit juice mixture to gelatin mixture and chill until almost set.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt, nuts, fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Add to chilled gelatin and refrigerate until firm.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices together 3 times.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add nuts, raisins egg and flour mixture alternately with applesauce, a small amount at a time.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Cook ground beef, potatoes and onions in skillet on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until done and potatoes are tender. Drain well. In a bowl, combine Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and pepper. Stir into beef mixture. Cook 2 to 5 minutes. Gently stir in tomatoes.

title: 1-2-3-4 biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender or your hands until you have fine crumbs.
Pour in the milk and stir until well blended.
Turn dough onto a floured surface; knead for one minute and roll or pat to about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with a floured cutter and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Serve warm.
(Brush the tops with butter if desired.)

title: taco salad(serves 8 or more)
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Add taco seasoning and water amount on taco seasoning package.
Add kidney beans.
Simmer.
Let cool.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: hermits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Put in an 8 x 11-inch pan (greased and floured).
Spread out with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: down-east clam chowder
directions: Fry salt pork in pot until light brown, add all other ingredients and a quart of water.
Cook slowly, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Corn dumplings could be added, if desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain.
Mash potatoes, add butter (melted), sugar and eggs (beat eggs), milk, nutmeg and vanilla flavor.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour filling in pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yum-Yum!!

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with meat.
Add crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown patties.
Remove patties from pan; pour off grease.
Stir into pan remaining soup and mushrooms.
Pour over meat in baking dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for about 35 minutes. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: homemade cereal
directions: Mix all together and toast until light brown in 350° oven. When cool, serve with milk.

title: poor man's hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet over medium heat, then drain meat mixture in colander and rinse with hot water to remove grease.
Pour meat back into skillet and add soup and paprika.
Simmer until heated through.
Remove from stove and stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add milk and fold in peanut butter.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt the butterscotch chips and butter or margarine. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm. Add and mix well the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Fold in until just combined the nuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, grapes, pineapple and nuts.
Mix dressing.
Add to chicken.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: ham spread
directions: Rinse 1 small can sauerkraut and mix in ham and cheese to taste.
Then add Miracle Whip to taste.
Serve on small rye or pumpernickel bread.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Soak bulgur
in
water	for
a few minutes. Squeeze dry between palms
of
hand.
Chop scallions, parsley and tomatoes fine.
Add	bulgur,
lemon	juice, olive oil and tamari sauce. Serve on pita bread.

title: grandma's freezer salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with whipped cream.
Place in 8 x 10-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.

title: stupid pie
directions: Add vanilla and sugar to egg whites.
Beat until smooth.
Add crackers, coarsely broken and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip and chill 2 or 3 hours.
Rich and delicious.

title: bo's beef or venison chili
directions: Brown chili meat that has been seasoned with garlic powder, black pepper and onion.
Add blended tomatoes and bring to a boil. Add French's Chili-O mix that has been mixed with 1 cup of water. Simmer on low for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: beef stir fry with tri-colored peppers
directions: Trim fat from beef, and cut crosswise into 1/4 inch slices. Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over high heat until hot. Add beef, soy sauce, and next 3 ingredients; stir fry 3 minutes or until beef is done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in broth and milk; heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add chicken and vegetables.* Line quiche dish with 1 crust (follow package directions).
Add chicken mixture and top with second crust.
Seal edges and cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party snacks
directions: Heat margarine, bacon drippings, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt and savory salt.
Mix cereal and nuts in large pan. Pour small amount of sauce over mixture and stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 250° in uncovered pan.
After cool, store in airtight container.

title: dressing
directions: Cube bread 2 or 3 days ahead to let it completely dry.
Run celery and onion through the food processor and then cook until it loses its green look.
Mix all together.
Mixture should be rather sloppy, so add enough broth or water to make it soupy.
Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until set up and slightly brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crust from bread.

Butter and cut into quarters. Alternate layers of bread and cheese in 11-1/2 x 7-1/2 x 1-1/2 buttered casserole beginning with bread and ending with cheese. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Let stand a few minutes, cut into squares and serve.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Pour over shrimp (in single layer on large flat baking pan).
Cook in a 350° oven for approximately 40 minutes.
Turn once with spatula after 20 minutes.
Serve with French bread for dunking sauce.
Bon Appetite.

title: corn relish
directions: In a bowl, combine drained corn and oil.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and celery seed.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add to corn mixture.
Cover and cool.
Refrigerate several hours.
Drain to serve.
Makes 3 cups.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk-soda mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts and prunes.
Bake in a well-greased pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
While cake is still hot, pour the icing over the cake.

title: gum drop bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar, add vanilla, then eggs.
Mix applesauce and water and add to creamed mixture gradually with flour mixture.
Stir in gumdrops, raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 325° oven.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O in boiling water.
Add other ingredients. Freeze.
Set out 4 hours before serving.
Pour 2 quarts ginger ale over when ready to serve.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Bring to boil the water, oleo, oil and cocoa and pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and soda; mix well and bake in greased oblong pan for 45 or 50 minutes at 275°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half and line the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, filling side up.
Sprinkle sliced bananas over Twinkies.
Prepare pudding according to directions and spread over Twinkies and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken salad with walnuts
directions: Dice chicken carefully into 3/4-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Mix celery, oranges, walnuts, parsley, mayo, salt and pepper together. Add chicken and toss gently to maintain whole pieces.
Try carefully not to break up the chicken pieces.

title: jane bain's chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water to cover.
Season with chopped celery, onion, salt and black pepper.
When tender, remove from bone and cut into bite sized pieces.
Measure and add same amount of chopped celery.
Mix with enough mayonnaise to hold together. Season with zestful seasoning.
Mix well.
Taste for seasoning, adding more zestful seasoning to taste.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, melted oleo and nuts.
Press half of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Boil vegetables (potatoes, carrots and onions) until almost done (potatoes should be firm); drain.
Prepare soup as directed on can.
Add vegetables and heat to boiling.
Add cheese slices. Stir until melted.
Serve.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook on low heat 1 to 2 hours.
Turn in Campbell's soup labels to St. Ann School!

title: apple cherry jello
directions: Mix together applesauce and cherry Jell-O; heat just to boiling. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Mix and refrigerate until set.

title: meme beckham's biscuits
directions: Measure flour in bowl.
Cut in shortening with two knives. Stir in milk.
Round up and pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together, except chicken pieces; let set for 1/2 hour. Grease casserole pan.
Pour in mixture.
Place sufficient chicken pieces on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is brown and done.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add soup, sour cream and milk to this.
Add cheese that has been cut up in squares.
Place in a 2-quart dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
You may also substitute with ham.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Have pie crust made and ready. Wash and cut rhubarb into small pieces. Add to pie shell, rounding to 1-inch deep. Combine sugar, flour, salt and jello. Mix well and sprinkle over rhubarb; dot with butter. Add top crust and make a few slits in the top crust with knife for air vents. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma's macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Drain and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Slice cheese and layer in macaroni saving enough to place on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecan halves on the bottom of the pie crust.
Beat the eggs.
Add butter, corn syrup and the vanilla.
Stir until well blended.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add pimentos.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tangy cocktail sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors. Makes about 1 cup.

title: banana chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in pan and bake for 34 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle nuts on top if you would like.

title: mexican hominy casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup with Cheddar cheese in saucepan and combine well.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle top with crushed corn chips.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook roast until done.
Cool; remove bones and fat.
Save juice from roast; add 1 cup juice, 1/3 cup vinegar, 2 tablespoons brown sugar, 1 onion, salt, pepper and 1 small bottle of ketchup. Simmer 2 hours or put in crock-pot and cook on low all day.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain grease; let cool.
Combine with lettuce, tomatoes, onion, cheese and kidney beans.
Just before serving, add taco chips and dressing.
Toss gently.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Boil pineapple and sugar to dissolve sugar and	pour over cake.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.	Sprinkle coconut and nuts over the top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in mixture (reserve 1 tablespoon flour).
Heat half the oil in large nonstick skillet.
Add chicken, cook 10 to 12 minutes, brown
on each side. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons chicken broth, if needed, to prevent sticking.
Remove and keep warm.
Add remaining oil and heat.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Saute 3 minutes.
Stir in 1 tablespoon reserved flour.
Cook 30 seconds.
Slowly stir in remaining chicken broth; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat. Place yogurt in bowl.
Stir in 2 tablespoons thickened mixture. Stir yogurt mixture into remaining mixture in skillet.
Add reserved chicken.
Heat through.
Serves 4.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in bowl in order listed.
You can make this the night before, but do not mix until just before serving!

title: english toffee(yields 20 servings)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and chopped almonds.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly to 290° on candy thermometer.
Pour in shallow pan to harden.
Cut into squares with your pizza cutter before it hardens.
Cover it with chocolate or dip and roll in chopped pecans.

title: lemon and garlic pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until done.
Drain and return to the hot pot.
Mince the garlic.
In a small pan heat the oil and butter.
Add the garlic and cook 1 minute.
Toss the garlic oil, parsley, zest and juice, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper with the pasta. Taste for seasoning and salt and pepper as needed.
Serve at once.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Combine beans, soup and cheese.
Pour into quart casserole. Top with onions and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in microwave for approximately 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add to Cool Whip and stir until well mixed.
Spoon into pie crust and place in refrigerator until cool.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: You will also need a Reynold's oven bag (large).

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate mixture until cold.
Shape into balls and roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Let dry overnight.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In 12-inch electric skillet over medium heat, heat 3/4 inch salad oil to 350°.

title: poached salmon or cod(kokt laks eller torsk)
directions: Place fillet (can be frozen) or steaks of fish in boiling water to cover.
For each quart of water add the listed ingredients. Heat to simmer and let steep until fish flakes easily.
Lift carefully with a slotted spoon.
Serve with melted butter mixed with finely chopped hard-boiled eggs and boiled potatoes.

title: garlic-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until medium soft; drain well.
Melt margarine in skillet and saute chopped onion.
Add garlic cheese. Add the mushroom soup.
In casserole dish, put a layer of broccoli and a layer of sauce.
Repeat.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into loaf pan; pack firmly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candy apples
directions: Boil sugar and syrup using enough water to dissolve.
Do not stir anymore.
Boil to 300°.
When at 300°, place wood skewers into stem end of bright red apples.
Dip into the candy syrup, then place on a large, well-greased pan with bottom of apple down. Apples dry in 15 minutes.
(Set pan of syrup in boiling water and dip after the boil is finished.)

title: fried catfish
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Soak fish pieces in milk for 1 hour.
Mix flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper and seasonings together. Drain fish and coat with cornmeal mixture.
Deep fry in oil at 375° a few pieces at a time until golden brown or pan-fry on both sides until lightly brown and done to your liking.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice from fruit and enough water to make 2 cups.
Let cool, then add the Coca-Cola.
When Jell-O begins to thicken, add fruits and nuts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water till it forms very hard piece when dropped in cold water. Add peanuts and stir constantly. Cook 10-12 minutes till mixture begins to turn brown. Add salt, butter and vanilla. Cook a little longer till mixture becomes a little darker. Then add soda. Mixture must be stirred quickly as it's removed from stove so it won't foam up and boil over. Pour on buttered cookie sheet. I don't flatten it much because all those little air bubbles keep it from getting too hard to eat. When cool, break into pieces.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, powdered alum and salt.
Add water and vegetable oil.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Knead, add food colorings.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Heat oleo until soft. Add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time and beat. Add flour, whipping cream and a good bit of lemon extract. Mix well. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix egg, sugars, syrup and vanilla.
Last, add pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Place meat in 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes; drain and stir in remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Re-cover. Microwave on simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until meat is fork-tender.
Blend in sour cream.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice on diced apples and stir.	Add celery, grapes, pineapple chunks and walnuts.
Mix Marzetti dressing with 1/4 cup pineapple juice, and add to fruit mixture.	Chill.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soups (undiluted).
Alternate chicken, tortillas, soup mix and cheese twice in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: german potato dumplings
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins the day before dumplings are to be made.
Before using, peel, wash and grate potatoes.
Add flour, eggs, butter and seasonings to potatoes and knead to a firm dough.
Toast bread and cut into cubes.
Shape dumpling mixture around bread cubes and drop into boiling water and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread i
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well. Fry sausage and crumble; drain very well. Mix all ingredients. Pour into a hot, oiled black iron skillet. Place in a 400° oven and bake until golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; remove any excess fat.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, brown sugar and oregano.
Boil 6 lasagna noodles.
Mix eggs with cottage cheese.

title: pa pa bailey's favorite syrup candy
directions: Combine syrups, butter and salt.
Cook until it forms a soft ball; gradually stir in peanuts, then add soda, stirring until it foams and pour into a prebuttered dish.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Then add flour, butter, syrup, coconut and pineapple.
Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and ham soup
directions: Combine onion, garlic and margarine in 3-quart casserole. Cook at High for three minutes until onion is tender.
Stir in ham, broth, broccoli, tomatoes and liquid, water and macaroni. Cover and cook on High for 15 minutes until boiling, stirring once to break up broccoli.
Cook at Medium for eight minutes until broccoli and macaroni are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle individual servings with grated Parmesan cheese. Serves 6.

title: ann's quick-serve ice cream
directions: Pour ingredients into a small Ziploc bag.
Then put ice and salt into a large Ziploc bag.
Add small bag into large and shake. Minutes later, you will have great ice cream.
This recipe may be doubled or more.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar, gradually stirring in milk.
Cook and stir until thick over low-medium heat.
Add margarine and amaretto; stir well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Dust with nutmeg and cool.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine
flours.
In
a large bowl thoroughly mix 2 1/2 cups flour mixture, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.

title: mexican corn soup
directions: Saute and stir butter, green pepper, green onion, garlic, oregano, pepper and flour in large pot.
Add chicken broth, salsa, bay leaf and corn.
Let simmer.
Serve warm with shredded cheese and tortilla chips crunched up on top.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Mix together oysters, milk, oyster liquid and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together butter, crackers and bread crumbs. Layer the mixture in a small casserole beginning with cracker crumb mix. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: sun-dried tomato dip
directions: Place tomatoes in a shallow dish; cover with vinegar.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Using food processor or sharp knife, chop tomatoes into bite size pieces.

Combine remaining ingredients. Serve at room temperature with pita chips, Italian bread or bagel chips, or toast thick slices of French bread, top with the dip and serve on a platter decorated with fresh parsley.

title: crisp cucumber pickles(may prepare ahead.  makes 4 jars.)
directions: Mix salt, onions and cut-up cucumbers.
Put in ice cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Pour in drained cucumbers and onions; add spices.
When the mixture comes to a boil, pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken-vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large shallow pan, pour Wish-Bone dressing over chicken.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover; raise oven temperature to 375°.
Turn chicken over; add vegetables and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, water, butter and corn syrup.
Cook until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Combine flour, cornstarch, granulated sugar, salt and mix thoroughly.
Add to scalded milk.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add hot butterscotch mixture; stir until smooth.
Stir a small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolks; return to double boiler and cook a few minutes longer.
Use 2 egg whites and 1/4 cup white sugar for meringue.

title: baked corn
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan and saute in the oil the onion. Blend in and cook, stirring for about 3 minutes, taking care not to brown the flour the flour, brown sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Add and continue to cook, stirring, until thick the milk.
Stir about 1 tablespoon of the heated sauce into eggs.
Add about 3 more tablespoons, one at a time, stirring after each addition.
This warms the eggs while keeping them liquid.
Once the eggs have been warmed in this fashion, pour them into the sauce and add, mixing well the corn.
Pour into an oven dish and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mother's cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Refrigerate until begins to congeal. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: penne al formaggio pecorino romano
directions: In a saute pan, over medium heat, heat the olive oil.
Add the garlic and cook for 2 minutes until fragrant.
Add the broccoli and saute for 1 minute.
Add the stock.
Raise the heat to high and cook until the liquid is almost evaporated, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Stir all together with 1 small bottle of creamy cucumber salad dressing.
Chill well.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Prick with fork and pour 1/3 cup lemon juice over the top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pinch chicken in pan.
Boil broccoli spears until tender. Place on top of chicken.
Mix soup and mayonnaise and pour over top of chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle paprika over this.
Put cheese on top of that and then crumble Ritz over top.
Bake in oven.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over crushed chips.
Top with cheese.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: crock-pot chicken and gravy
directions: Make chicken gravy mix according to directions (microwave is easiest) and pour in crock-pot.
Or pour prepared gravy into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Place frozen chicken in gravy.
Cover and cook on low 7 hours.
Serve over cooked egg noodles or rice.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and let stand 1 hour. Pour in ginger ale and serve over ice.
Yields 50 to 60 servings.

title: haywood alaskan stew
directions: Brown meat in butter and shortening.
Season with garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Mix potatoes, carrots, tomato juice and meat.
Cook until carrots are tender.

title: spinach, radish and cashew salad
directions: Toss with the following dressing.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Layer a baking dish with bacon. Cover with sliced potatoes. Cover with onions.
Dot 1 can of cream of celery soup on top of onions and cover with foil. Bake at 300° until potatoes are done, about 45 minutes. Cover with Velveeta cheese and let melt. Stir all together.

title: holiday potato dish
directions: Remove skins from potatoes; shred into bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup melted butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese; mix well. Turn in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cornflakes and drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Garnish with pimiento and parsley.

title: decadent almond bars
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar and butter.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Blend. Add 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
