Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with rest of almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into bars.
Delicious!

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until smooth.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: mr. hampton's pound cake
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until golden brown.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Sift the flour and measure.
Add cocoa, salt and sugar and sift together.
Add Crisco, food coloring, vanilla and 2/3 cup buttermilk and beat.
Add eggs and remaining buttermilk.
Beat 1 minute.
Mix in vinegar and soda by hand.
Bake at 350° on first rack above the middle for 30 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add soup and sour cream; mix well.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: creamed chicken and noodles
directions: Cook soup as directed on can.
Set aside.
Cook noodles 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.
Drain.
Mix chunk chicken with noodles.
Pour in cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.

title: linguine noodles
directions: Cook linguine 9 minutes. Drain and mix with other ingredients. Mix together with hands.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Soften the cream cheese; add the condensed milk and mix well. Add the lemon juice and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Fill the pie shell with the filling; cover the top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: gloria's award winning cheesecake
directions: Allow cream cheese, sour cream and butter to come to room temperature. In a large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients except eggs. Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.

title: shrimp and crab meat salad
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place 2/3 of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Spread broccoli over crumbs. Pour chicken soup over broccoli.
Spread Cheddar cheese next. Spread chestnuts over cheese; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in oil.
Sift flour and salt together and add to oil and water mixture.
Knead until smooth. Shape into ball and grease bowl and dough with oil.
Let rise 10 to 25 minutes.
This makes 2 (12-inch) pizzas.
Finish with your favorite toppings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in a tight container.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Cream together Jell-O and cream cheese. Add water; mix well. Refrigerate until almost set.
Add carrot, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Cut Jack cheese into strips. Stuff into seeded chilies, folding or tucking cheese inside. Arrange in single layer in shallow greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: fruit cake(maude hart)
directions: Roll fruit and nuts in flour and add all other ingredients. Bake very slowly at approximately 250° or 300°.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue mixing until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add bananas, oatmeal and nuts, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and blend.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove cookies from pan at once.

title: tutti-frutti lemon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine undrained pineapple tidbits, mandarin orange sections (undrained), fruit cocktail (undrained), coconut and lemon juice.
Sprinkle the instant pudding mix over fruits and toss lightly to mix.
Chill.
Just before serving, peel and slice bananas, fold into lemon fruit mixture.
Serve in dessert dishes, top with topping, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt, sugar, nutmeg and vanilla.
Beat slowly until well mixed.
Add scalding hot milk.
Stir well.
Pour into crust and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until a silver knife inserted (1-inch from side) comes out clean.
The center may still look soft, but will set later.
Be careful not to bake too long.

title: ham-vegetable chowder
directions: Cook broccoli with sauce in pouch according to package directions.
In saucepan, combine cooked broccoli with corn and ham.
Stir in cream and cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: afton's bread
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast lightly.
Let set 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add to yeast mixture along with salt. Then add 6 cups flour and stir with wooden spoon.
Add 6 more cups of flour and stir well.
Add more flour to make a workable dough (2 to 4 cups).
Knead dough.
Let it raise until double in size; punch down.
Let it raise again.
Dump out and cut with sharp knife into 5 loaves.
Work the air out of each and put in greased loaf pans.
Cover with a towel.
Let them rise.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 25 minutes at 350°.
Brush hot tops with butter for soft crust.

title: texas dip
directions: Blend oil and spices.
Add rest of ingredients and blend. Chill several hours before serving.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: fresh tomato gravy
directions: In a saucepan, cook tomatoes in 2 cups of water until tender. Set aside. Using an iron skillet, add meat drippings and heat until hot. Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring until it makes a smooth, brown paste. Slowly add tomatoes and sugar. Let boil until it thickens. Delicious served hot over biscuits or rice. You can make this gravy by using canned tomatoes or tomato paste.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into 3 or 4 rolls.
Place on foil covered cookie sheet and cover with wax paper. Refrigerate for 3 days.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning after 40 minutes of baking time.

title: sweet spanish onion quiche
directions: Bake pie shell in a 375° oven for 7 minutes, until partially done.

title: honey icing
directions: Add all ingredients.
Blend with fork until smooth.
Makes 1 cup icing.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Filling:
Chicken, green onions and Jack cheese in large bowl.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to package directions for empty baked crust.
Cool.
In a small saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups of peaches and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Continue to cook 4 to 5 minutes until peaches are soft.
Cool.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pint size jar. Cover jar tightly and shake well.
Use immediately or store in refrigerator until it is ready to use.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle dry jello over rhubarb, then sprinkle sugar over jello.
Next, sprinkle dry cake mix in the pan.
Pour melted butter and then boiling water. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate and hot water; refrigerate while mixing other ingredients.
Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff.
Set aside egg whites.
Mix margarine, salt, vanilla, sugar and baking soda, then add chocolate, flour and buttermilk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan lined with waxed paper.

title: stuff(main dish casserole)
directions: Place ground beef into cold electric skillet; add a layer of thin sliced onion, a layer of thin potatoes, thin layer of carrots, cabbage and celery.
Repeat if necessary, then add creamed soup (undiluted), salt and pepper to taste.
Place skillet on medium heat with lid on until valve pops (if lid has a valve). If not, when light goes off.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Can simmer much longer as a casserole.

title: mother's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted together dry ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix ingredients well except brown sugar and pecans or coconut. Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle brown sugar and nuts or coconut over top.
Bake 40 minutes.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch large cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with the buttermilk.

title: crab-dip caliente
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, salad dressing mix and lemon juice until smooth.
Stir in jalapeno, tomato, green onions and crabmeat.
Spoon mixture into a small casserole dish and bake 15 minutes.
Remove and garnish.
Serve with fresh bread or crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Put chocolate bits, egg and instant coffee into blender. Blend on low speed.
Heat 1 cup of milk until near boiling.
Add to blended ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour into individual serving dishes and refrigerate until cold.
Top with whipped cream to serve.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together first 5 items; put on cookie sheet on top shelf of oven and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and crumble up.

title: uncooked fondant
directions: Place egg white, water and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat with fork.
Add confectioners sugar gradually stirring until mixture is very stiff.
Add coloring or additional flavoring if desired. Remove from bowl; knead on board lightly dusted with confectioners sugar until smooth.
Makes 1 pound.

title: hillary's chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla in large bowl until creamy.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop on baking sheets; bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on sheets for short time; cool on wire rack for 2 minutes.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar, jello and white sugar. Arrange rhubarb on top. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over rhubarb. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Immediately turn upside-down on foil. Serve with whipped cream.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put 2 cups of sifted bread flour in a bowl with yeast, sugar and salt.
Pour warm milk, warm water and margarine into bowl.
Mix with electric mixer 2 minutes, gradually add other flour until dough is kneadable.
Put in another bowl and let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Punch down now and make into rolls.
Place on a biscuit pan and let rise again, about 30 minutes.
Now bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Butter tops and eat.
You'll need some jelly.

title: sourdough cooking
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and yeast in large mixing bowl. Gradually stir in very warm water until mixture resembles a smooth paste.

Cover with clean cloth and let stand in a warm place (85°) to sour and bubble for 2 to 3 days, stirring several times a day. At the end of souring period, pour in large jar or plastic container partially covered to allow gases to escape.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy turkey broccoli dinner
directions: Place broccoli in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix turkey, soup, dressing and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli.
Top with combined stuffing mix and margarine.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan crunch dessert
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and egg.
Spread onto a cookie sheet that has been lined with foil and greased.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool and crumble.
Mix pudding mix, sour cream and milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place half of pecan mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then sliced bananas.
Pour pudding mixture over bananas and top with remaining pecan crunch mix.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix and pour in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Use Pam or oil and flour pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water and chill until firm (done individually).
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup water and add hot pineapple juice; cool.
Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Add pineapple juice mixture.
Cut jello into small squares and fold into cream mixture.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Chill for 6 to 12 hours before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water in a quart saucepan.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened, but not set (15 to 25 minutes).
Fold in strawberries.
Turn into the pie shell.
Chill until firm, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ketchup
directions: Quarter tomatoes and remove stems.
Add peppers, seeds removed, and slice in strips.
Add chopped onions.
Place 1/3 in blender or food processor; mix until smooth.
Repeat until all tomatoes are blended.
Add vinegar, salt, sugar and spices, tied loosely in muslin bag.
Simmer, uncovered, until mixture is reduced to 1/2.
Pour into hot jars and cover loosely with lids. Process at 212° for 10 minutes.
Remove and tighten lids.
Makes 5 pints.

title: eggplant meatless balls
directions: Cook eggplant for 10 minutes.
Strain and squeeze.
Mix rest of ingredients together and form into small balls.
Fry in oil or bake in a 350° oven. Good luck!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, water and pudding together.
Fold in whipping cream. Layer vanilla wafers on bottom of dish.
Top with pudding mix. Repeat layers.

title: bloop-bloop pudding(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Fill large pot with water and put in unopened cans.
Make sure the water covers them.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Cook undrained pineapple and jello in saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and whipped topping and mix together.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle nuts. Refrigerate until firm and serve.

title: barbecued beans
directions: These are elongated tubers, part of a hardy sunflower, in no way related to the globe artichoke.
They have beige skins and crisp white flesh.
Select firm unblemished tubers with no soft spots.
Will keep in a plastic bag in refrigerator up to 1 week. Scrub well.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl mix stuffing mix with milk and mayonnaise. Set aside 1/2 cup of stuffing mixture.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour the mixture into baking dish and top with stuffing, that you set aside.
Bake at 350° for one half hour.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Continue to use mixer, adding dry ingredients and vanilla. Use a spoon to mix in pecans and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes in regular oven. Makes about 70 cookies.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Sift flour, soda and spices. Combine flour mixture with applesauce mixture; stir in raisins and nuts. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. May be baked in two layer pans and frost with caramel icing.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Grate cheese.
Bring water, wine, margarine and seasonings to boil.
Add cheese and set in double boiler (use stainless steel or ceramic pot).
Stir thoroughly with wooden spoon until cheese melts into heavy sauce.
Add more wine if too thick.
Add more cheese if too thin.
Dice bread in 2-inch squares and toast lightly in oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake in loaf pan at 350 degrees for 45 min. Bake longer for darkness.

title: swiss steak
directions: Wipe meat with cold, damp cloth.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Pound into steak.
Cut meat into 2-inch squares.
Brown meat and onion in fat in heavy pan.
Add green peppers, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add more liquid if needed during cooking.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Makes a medium stiff dough.
Break off enough to make a 3-inch ball.
Roll out into round shape, 1/8-inch thick.
Cook on dry grill or in iron skillet until browned on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add vanilla, pecans and flour.
Roll in small balls a little larger than marbles.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 30 minutes in 300° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar, cool. Roll in sugar again.

title: smoked sausage and potato bake
directions: Pare and cut potatoes into eighths.
In saucepan, cover with water; add salt and boil until slightly tender.
Drain.
Stir butter into potatoes until melted.
Add green pepper, if desired. Pour potatoes into greased baking dish.
Cut sausage links into individual serving pieces and place on top of potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven until sausage is browned and sizzling.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add nuts, sugar, milk and coconut.
Roll in balls about size of walnut.
Chill.
In double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate.
Dip balls in warm paraffin and chocolate mixture, using toothpicks.
Put on wax paper to harden.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine and sugar; add eggs and remaining ingredients. Cook in unbaked pie crust for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel fingers
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend. Sift in flour and mix well.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan lined with wax paper.

title: carolina coleslaw
directions: Mix sugar, celery seed,
dry mustard, salt, vinegar and vegetable oil in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage, pepper and onion.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Keep in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place layer of coarsely chopped chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix undiluted soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs mixed with poppy seed. Pour the melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Can use 4 chicken breasts.
Serves 12.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water and eggs. Add 2 cups rhubarb. Pour into a 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle the rest of the rhubarb on top. Sprinkle the sugar on. Pour the whipping cream on top. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool completely. Refrigerate.

title: surprise salad
directions: Heat pineapple and pour Jell-O in it; cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Can add chopped nuts to give it crunch. Mix well and cool.

title: reiter biscuits
directions: In bowl, mix flour and buttermilk to a sticky consistency. Pour oil into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scoop out with hands the amount of finger length size.
Drop onto oiled pan.
Roll over biscuit in oil.
Push to side of pan.
Continue until all dough is used up to make sure a little oil is in pan.
Still bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Let dinner rolls thaw out.
Cut each roll in half.
Smash roll out and wrap the pepperoni chunk and Mozzarella cheese inside it. Roll each pepperoni roll into melted margarine.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Make sure you turn them over halfway into baking time.

title: mom's scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake about an hour at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy and well blended. Add eggs and beat well. Add pineapple and bread cubes. Gently blend all together. Bake, uncovered, in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°. Serve hot.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding flour until dough is almost as stiff as pie crust.
Fry in deep fat, very hot.

title: u.p. style ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size pieces. Place ribs meat side up in a roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325 degrees: drain.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Melt oleo and mix with potatoes.
Add sugar, salt, milk and flavoring.
Beat eggs and fold in.
Pour into greased souffle baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour together well.
Sprinkle over souffle mix.
Pour 1/3 cup melted oleo over this and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: croissant rolls
directions: Dip biscuit in melted oleo, roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Give a quick twist.
Bake as directed on can.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pistachio pudding.
Add nuts; fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Microwave corn for 3 minutes per ear on High.
Cool for 3 minutes.
Using gloves, peel off shucks and silk.
Butter each ear; pop back in microwave for 30 seconds per ear.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, egg, butter and vanilla.
Beat smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup walnuts, turn into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Take from oven.
Arrange marshmallows, walnuts and chocolate over top.
Return pan for 2 minutes or until chocolate is soft.
Swirl chocolate over marshmallows and walnuts.
Cool.

title: orange glazed carrots(low-fat)
directions: Steam carrots 15 to 20 minutes, leaving them slightly crunchy. Set aside.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook according to directions (omit butter, brown in oil instead); cool.
Add green olives, artichoke hearts, green onions, green pepper, curry powder and mayonnaise.

title: dump cake
directions: Place each ingredient in order as listed in an oblong casserole, layer on layer (8 x 10 or 9 x 13). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In pretty glass bowl (2-quart), cover bottom and sides with 5 slices of cake.
Layer half of the strawberries.

Drizzle 2 tablespoons orange juice. Add half of the vanilla pudding, then a layer of topping. Repeat layer with remaining cake, strawberries, orange juice and pudding, ending with topping. Garnish with whole berries with stems on. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll cheese ball in chopped ham.
Let chill.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: easy chili pie
directions: Layer 1/2
chips,
onion, half of cheese and chili in 1 1/2 quart
casserole.
Top
with
remaining chips and bake in preheated
oven
at 375° about 25 minutes.	Top with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: summer soup
directions: Boil green beans, potatoes, onion and corn until tender; drain.
Add milk to cover vegetables.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Heat until butter melts.
Do not boil.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Pour sugar over cranberries, pineapple, orange peel and pecans.
Set this aside.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs and oil until well blended.
Add strawberries and beat until berries are partly broken up.
Add flour mixture and beat until batter is smooth.
Bake in a greased 9 x 15-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and turn out on racks.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Mix with less than half of the container of Cool Whip. Layer in bottom of cake pan and press down.

title: my mom's artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes somewhat; separate leaves. Mix all ingredients. Microwave 2 minutes. Rotate and microwave 2 more minutes. Put under broiler to brown. Serve with Wheat Thins or your favorite crunchy!

title: carrot pineapple loaf
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix sugar and oil.
Add carrots, pineapple, vanilla and eggs plus egg whites. Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(This recipe is from Washington State Heart Association.)

title: mexican chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Boil spaghetti and drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese, rotel tomatoes and mushroom soup in a saucepan on low heat.
When melted, add chopped chicken breast and simmer on low about 10 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti and stir to mix. Simmer on low an additional 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: If using frozen broccoli, do not boil.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 400° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: maple pralines
directions: Put sugar, syrup and cream in saucepan.
Boil to soft-ball stage (234°).
Let stand until cool.
Add pecans.
Beat with wooden spoon.
Drop onto buttered pan or waxed paper from spoon.

title: "susie's" chocolate pie(the best!)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, eggs, flour and cocoa.
Beat.
Add milk.
Put in double boiler and boil until thick.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat thoroughly with electric mixer.
Cool.
Place in a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in oven at 300° for about 20 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: mouse salad
directions: Drain pears. Arrange lettuce on plates.

Place pear half on lettuce bed. Place two cloves for eyes. Using toothpick, spear on toothpick for nose. Make carrot curls using peeler; attach carrot curl onto mouse with toothpick for tail. Cut marshmallows into slices. Spear them with toothpicks for ears.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in an ungreased 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: iowa governor's apricot almond dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, reserving 1/3 cup for topping.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, press 1/2 mixture in bottom firmly.
Add 1 quart ice cream.
Put in freezer to refirm.
When firm, coat with 10 ounces of apricot jam.
Repeat layers and top with crumb mixture that was set aside.
Put in freezer.
Cut in squares and serve in sherbet glasses.
Top with a cherry.
Serves 12.

title: sour noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box; drain.
In blender, mix vinegar, salt and pepper, sugar, parsley flakes, mustard, onion, garlic powder and cucumber; liquify.
Add Crisco oil.
Pour over drained noodles and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar in a bowl.
In a larger bowl, mix the All-Bran and the milk.
Let stand a minute and grease muffin pans.
Add egg, vegetable oil and molasses.
Beat well.
Add raisins and flour mixture to the second mixture and mix until flour is absorbed.
Place in muffin pans and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O.
Cool.
Add other ingredients. Chill.

title: icebox coffee cake
directions: Mix together yeast, 1/2 teaspoon flour, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 cup warm milk and let rise to top of cup.
Beat eggs and add 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 cup warm milk.
Combine with yeast mixture. Mix 4 cups flour, 1 teaspoon salt and butter to make like a pie crust.
Combine to the other mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut dough into 4 or 5 parts.
Roll out like pie crust. Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts on it.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut half way through. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: beer potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes as if for scalloped potatoes.
Add chopped onion, celery and sliced mushrooms; place in center of two large sheets of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle on bacon bits and season with pepper.
Fold corners of foil to the center and build the sides up to make a small dish. Pour in beer and close the foil package.
Place on hot grill for about 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Wash, dry and cut mushrooms.
Saute mushrooms and onions in melted butter.
Stir in flour and cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth gradually until it comes to a boil.
Add other ingredients and cool about 30 minutes or until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: aunt millwee's peanut brittle
directions: Cook until honey color. Do not stir.
Pour into long pan.
Let cool. Break into pieces.

title: nacho bean dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning together.
Spread out in bottom of 9
X 13-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream.
Spread on top layer of beans.
Sprinkle shredded taco cheese on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: freda's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together above 5 ingredients in the pan you are baking in.
Use 8 x 8-inch size.
Make three wells in the mixture.
In one part, put 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In 2nd well, put 1 teaspoon vinegar and in the 3rd, put 1/4 pound of melted oleo.
On top of all this, pour 1 cup cold water.
Stir until well blended and smooth.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, ice with favorite icing.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in roaster.
Put chicken over rice and season to taste.
Mix soup, water and cream cheese together.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and rice.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 3 hours.
Uncover for the last 1/2 hour.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening and salt to boiling water.
Lower heat and boil until shortening melts.
Remove from heat.
Add flour all at once and stir until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each egg.
Drop or shape onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°, then lower heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.
Makes 1 dozen dessert size puffs.
Fill with pudding.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasonings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix altogether except oleo.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Add 1/2 stick oleo, broken up, on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes (or less depending on oven).

title: old fashioned cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.	Add milk and egg small amount at a time.
Handle lightly.
Roll out. Spread butter, cinnamon and brown sugar on.
Cut and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker icebox pie
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers. Next, layer pudding. Then repeat graham cracker and pudding layers until you are at the top of pan. Top with cherry pie filling and Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: polish wedding sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Scald with boiling water; drain.
In a saucepan, combine lard and flour into paste.
Add water slowly until thin sauce is made.
Add vinegar, sugar and pepper; pour over cabbage and cook until tender.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan combine flour, salt, mustard, pepper and margarine.
Add milk and thicken.
Add 1 cup cheese to mixture, stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Pour mixture over macaroni in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add chunks of cheese, if desired.
Garnish with herb stuffing mix and bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients plus 1 egg, then add 1 egg at a time, beating after each egg. Beat till smooth add poppy seeds. Bake in greased, sugared bundt pan for 1 hour at 325° to 350°. (Cake shrinks away from side of pan when done.) Turn out at once on a rack to cool.

title: snicker bar cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients, except candy bars, for 30 seconds on low speed.
Then 3 minutes on high. Stir in chopped candy bars.
Pour batter into 2 greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine and drain orange pulp and pineapple.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add fruit juice with gelatin and sugar.
Cool, then add mixture. Chill. Serves 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and put half in greased pan, then add hash browns and rest of mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Top with corn flakes and bake for 10 minutes longer until brown on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice and chicken in large casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and water in bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french bread
directions: In a
mixing
bowl, sprinkle yeast over 2 1/2 cups cool water and
stir to dissolve.
After about 3 minutes, add about 4 cups flour.
Mix
well
and
stir
vigorously
for about 10 minutes. Dissolve
salt
in	2 teaspoons water and add to the batter.
Stir to mix well.

title: abalone cocktail
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Chop about 3 to 4 peppers (1/3 cup).
Add about 2 to 3 teaspoons of pepper juice.
(Suit to your taste.)
Remember the longer it sits, the hotter it gets.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pickled vegetables
directions: Place vegetables in large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with 3/4 cup of vinegar to 1/4 cup water.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.

title: hawaiian cup cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add the rest of ingredients with creamed butter and sugar.
Put into paper lined cupcake pans. Fill half full.
Bake at 350 degrees about 25 minutes.
Makes 25 - 30.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: Mix everything but berries and cook over low heat until clear, stirring constantly.
Cool.
When cold, mix in the berries and pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: hershey pie
directions: Put pudding in large bowl, add enough milk to Eagle Brand milk to make 2 cups.
Add vanilla and beat on high for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and Hershey bar.
Put in baked graham cracker shell. Garnish with grated Hershey bar.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: perfect dessert(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Mix all together. Add large container Cool Whip. Chill in covered casserole.

title: quick green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and mushroom soup; top with dried onion rings.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: bagel crisps
directions: Using a sharp serrated knife, halve bagels to make 2 semicircles.
Slice horizontally into 1/8-inch thick slices. Place in a single layer on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush both sides lightly with oil and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake at 400°
for about 12 minutes, or until crisp and light golden.

title: turkey casserole creation
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Blend well and turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with potato chips. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup or chicken broth

title: butternut raisin bread
directions: Combine flour, soda and raisins.
Stir well and set aside. Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Stir in squash, honey, water, spices and salt.
Add flour mixture.
Stir just until the ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into 3 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Makes 3 loaves. Batter may be baked in 3 greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook hamburger with onion.
Remove from heat and drain.
Mix with 1/2 can soup, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasoning. Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Top with mashed potatoes and remaining soup.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Add cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together; cream butter, sugar and egg (more shortening makes shorter cookies).
Add dry ingredients with milk and vanilla.
Roll out dough on board.
Cut in desired shape.
Bake
at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chilled tomatoes eminces
directions: If whole tomatoes are used, put through medium grinder or chop fine.
If using canned tomatoes, process in blender if desired. Add all other ingredients.
Blend and then chill to just short of freezing.
Stir well and serve in chilled cups.
Garnish with 1 teaspoon sour cream.
Sprinkle with chopped mint leaves.
If dried mint leaves are used, rub between hands and dust over surface of tomatoes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next five ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount boiling water until tender; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella. `Place half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the Ricotta cheese filling.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.

title: maple-walnut corn sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brush two 7-stick corn stick pans generously with oil.
Place in oven for about 5 minutes until hot.

title: diabetics peach-ginger ale mold salad
directions: Drain
peaches and set aside 1/2 cup. Arrange remaining peaches in bottom of 1 1/2 quart mold, overlapping the slices. Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.	Add ginger ale and chill until slightly
thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Chop the reserved 1/2 cup peach slices and fold into gelatin along with the walnuts.
Spoon
gelatin
mixture
over
peaches
in mold. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Unmold and serve.
(One cup each serving may be exchanged for 1 fruit.)

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Mix apples and cinnamon. Combine flour, shortening and milk. Roll in a jelly roll, filling with apples. Pour water and sugar (dissolved) over pie. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and margarine; reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture on bottom and 2 inches up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Spread topping over crumbs; top with softened ice cream or frozen yogurt. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs, pressing lightly.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping, cherries and Oreo cookies, if desired.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: In saucepan, blend milk into flour, stir constantly over medium heat until mixture is like thick paste.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Beat flour and milk mixture until very smooth.
Add to creamed mixture and beat to whipped consistency (10 minutes).
Add vanilla and food coloring.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese with fork and room temperature.
Add onion soup mix; rinse shrimp and mix in.
Slowly add sour cream to right consistency.
If made the night before, cheese will stiffen so add more sour cream before serving.
Best to let set overnight for stronger serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lemon raisin spread
directions: In saucepan, mix together sugar, egg, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add mayonnaise, pecans and raisins.
Chill well.
Serve with Ritz or other crackers.
Will serve about 20 and will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Blend beef, egg, onion and bread crumbs.
Set aside.
Mix soup, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Blend 1/3 soup mixture with meat mixture.
Shape into 6 oblong patties.
Brown in skillet.
Add water to remaining soup mixture.
Pour over browned patties.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, meat and gravy in same pot.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken seasoned with salt and pepper. You can use broth from chicken or buy broth in a can. Cook until chicken is tender. Let cool and take off bones. Put chicken and broth in pot and bring to a boil. Slice the flour tortillas; break and drop into chicken and broth. Reduce heat to medium and cook until tortillas are tender.

title: hot sauce
directions: Add the last 8 ingredients to the vegetables; put in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until desired thickness is reached.
Refrigerate or place in hot jars.
Seal. Cover with water and boil 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 pints.

title: monterey chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise, then dip in breadcrumbs until evenly coated. In a 13 x 9 baking dish, arrange chicken. Bake 15 minutes; top with salsa, then cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and chicken is no longer pink. serves 4.

title: never fail brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes (exactly).

title: butternut squash and cranberries
directions: Mix squash with eggs and 3 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in sugar, cranberries, salt and pepper.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Drizzle on rest of melted butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef, beans and rice skillet
directions: Cook rice and tomatoes until almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes. Then add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes, covered. (Or cook on high heat for 5 minutes then turn off heat.
Leave on unit for about 30 minutes.)

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar. Cook over low heat about 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and continue cooking and stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat. Cool. Add confectioners sugar, about 2 cups, gradually until of right consistency to spread. Good on Happy Day Yellow Cake.

title: sauce for broccoli
directions: Mix ingredients with rotary beater; bring to a boil slowly. Serve with broccoli.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs.
Stir in Bisquick, cinnamon and raisins.
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness; cut out.
Pour some corn oil on cookie sheet. Cover both sides of biscuits in oil.
Bake in a 400° to 450° oven for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: don't believe it's rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients.
Put in muffin tins. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Blend well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up bacon and fry and drain.
Brown ground beef with chopped onion and drain.
Mix all the beans together with juice. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Cream the cheese and add eggs, one at a time, then 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes until top cracks.
Remove from oven and let top fall (about 5 minutes).
Mix 1 cup sugar and sour cream.
Using this, fill center of tart and put back into oven for 5 minutes, then refrigerate.
Decorate top with cherries or filling.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Combine any one of the pie fillings with the other four ingredients.
Stir until completely blended.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: salmon quesadillas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Lightly butter one side of each tortilla.
Place tortilla, butter side down, in skillet over medium heat.
Drop 1/4
salmon mixture onto one half of tortilla. Cover with mozzarella cheese.
Fold tortilla in two and brown each side.
Repeat for remaining 3 tortillas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dilly bread(1 good size loaf)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add warm cheese. Add other ingredients and use enough flour to make a stiff dough. Beat well. Butter tops. Set in a warm place to rise. When double in bulk, about 1 hour, beat down with spoon and place in well buttered loaf pan. Butter top and bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes. Increase heat to 350° and bake until well browned, about 15 to 20 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: cabbage and ground turkey soup
directions: You will need a 4-quart stockpot to start.
Chop garlic and saute in oil.
Add turkey and brown with Worcestershire.
When meat is done, add cabbage and onion and saute for 5 minutes.
Add bouillon and dissolve.
Add tomatoes.
Add pepper and basil.
Add water and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes good soup for a cool day!

title: braided chili loaf
directions: In a skillet, heat oil.
Saute onion until soft.
Stir in the beef and break up while browning; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder, basil, cumin, pepper and salt.
Cook a few minutes, until sauce is absorbed.
Set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Place in a greased dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350°.

title: cream cheese candy
directions: Mix together cream cheese and almond flavor.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar.
Knead until no longer sticky.
Shape into 3/4 inch thick balls.
Roll balls in remaining powdered sugar.
Set balls in candy papers.
Let dry at room temperature. Store loosely covered in fridge.
Makes 6-7 dozen candies.

title: easy crockpot chinese-style pork ribs
directions: Combine soy sauce, marmalade, catsup and garlic. Brush on both sides of ribs. Place in crockpot. Pour remaining sauce over all. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Yield: 4-6 servings.

title: overnight cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle pie filling on top of rolls.
Melt together margarine with brown and white sugar and drizzle over pie filling.
Cover with towel overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crystal's sugar cookies
directions: Mix in a large bowl oil, sugar, egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to oil mixture, 1 cup at a time, until everything is together.
Mix well.
Shape on ungreased cookie sheet.
(May add sprinkles on cookies.) Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well; bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in preheated oven at 350°.

title: angel cake
directions: Sift flour with 3/4 cup sugar two times. Set aside. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar, salt and vanilla till stiff enough to form soft peaks; but still moist and glassy. Add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tbsp. at a time, continuing to beat until egg whites hold stiff peaks. Sift about 1/4 of flour mixture over whites fold in. Repeat by 1/4. Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 375 for 35-40 minutes or until done. Invert cake in pan and cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the chopped pecans and coconut.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread with the marshmallow cream while cake is hot.
Chill.

title: macaroni cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni 6 minutes, drain. In 2 qt. saucepan, melt margarine over low heat. Stir in flour and salt, stir until smooth. Gradually stir in milk until smooth, stirring constantly, cook over medium heat about 5 minutes. Cut Velveeta cheese up into 1/4 inch slices and add to mixture while cooking over medium/ low heat. Leave about 4 oz. of the Velveeta uncooked for topping to be added later. Continue cooking mixture for another 15 minutes over medium/low heat or until cheese has melted into the mixture. Grease a 2 qt. casserole dish with margarine and pour in drained macaroni and slowly pour in cheese mixture, blend well. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes, remove from heat and add remaining cheese on top, return to oven and heat about 5 to 8 minutes, until cheese melts. Do not stir. Enjoy the best cheesy macaroni you have ever eaten.

title: dot's blueberry bread
directions: Pat dry the blueberries; set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar together.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add dry ingredients, then add milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: sunny italy house dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Add water to egg whites and whip until frothy.
Add nuts and mix until all are covered.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread out pecan halves on a well-greased cookie sheet.
(Put all right side up to start.)
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple spritzer
directions: Rinse off the apple and remove the core.
Cut the apple in quarters.
Put 3 ice cubes in each of the 4 tall glasses.
Add 1 cup of apple juice and 1/2 cup seltzer water to each glass.
Add apple quarter to each glass and serve with a straw.

title: chicken cassandra(for crock-pot)
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry.
In skillet, saute chicken in Italian salad dressing over medium heat.
Mix rice, tomatoes, wine, seasonings and Brussels sprouts in crock-pot.
Top with chicken. Cover.
Cook on low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: layered green salad
directions: Arrange in layers in large bowl in the order listed: lettuce, celery, pepper, onion and peas.
Seal top with mayonnaise. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Seal and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours or overnight.
When serving, dip down through all layers; do not mix.

title: authentic mexican rice
directions: Boil garlic and mash it into a paste; set aside.
Brown rice in oil.
Add onion and garlic paste.
Add Chinese parsley.
Add tomatoes and cook until softened into rice mixture.
Add water. Stir in broth, carrot, peas, corn and diced meat.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and steam on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Buen Provecho!

title: salmon cakes
directions: Beat eggs in a medium sized bowl.
Add all ingredients except butter and salmon.
Mix well.
Flake salmon into mixture and stir until blended.
Melt butter in skillet.
Shape salmon mixture into patties and fry over medium heat until golden brown (about 5 minutes).
Yield:
6 patties.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings and discard tips.
Place wings on broiler pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes, turning once.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt 1 1/2 packages chocolate.
Mix eggs, corn syrup, cream and vanilla in blender until smooth.
With blender running, add cream cheese slowly.
Blend until smooth.
Mix in chocolate. Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until it sets. Cool on rack in oven.
Cover and chill.
Melt remaining chocolate and drizzle on top.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, flour, lemon flavoring and 7-Up together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Use large tube or Bundt pan.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown meat and onions in fat, drain.
Put in greased casserole with other ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown about 1 pound ground meat, drain and place in casserole dish.
Layer chilies, onion and cheese.
Pour creamed corn on top and spread to seal.

title: frozen bananas
directions: Peel bananas and cut them in half, crosswise.
Insert popsicle stick into each banana half.
Melt chocolate morsels in saucepan over low heat or put in microwave on High for 1 minute (the morsels will keep their shape until stirred).
Add milk to chocolate and stir until mixture is smooth.
Dip each banana in melted chocolate and roll it in pecans.
Place bananas on a plate covered with wax paper or plastic; freeze for 3 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and garlic to a boil. Serve over cooked pasta, celery, olives, cheese, onions and salami.
Dressing is also ideal for bean salad.

title: lucy's favorite strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in hot milk, let cool.
Fold Cool Whip into marshmallow mixture.
Mix boiling water and Jello, stir well, add strawberries and set until thick.
Crush crackers and line bottom of large glass pan.
Pour in set jello mixture, then marshmallow mixture.
Top with a few crumbs.

title: heavenly rice (1)
directions: Mix first four ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and turn to low heat for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let it stand for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Combine and mix sausage and cheese.
Mix well.
Add paprika, then biscuit mix; beat well.
Roll into small balls and put on cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli 15 minutes in a little salted water.
Add chicken soup, water, thyme, bacon, onion and cheese.
Blend well. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chicken quesadillas and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cook chicken in nonstick skillet until done and juices evaporate, stirring often. Add soup and salsa and heat through. Spread about 1/3 cup soup mixture on half of each tortilla to within 1/2-inch of edge. Moisten edge with water; fold over and seal. Place on baking sheets. Bake 5 minutes or until hot. Sprinkle with cheese and let melt. Serve with sour cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large frying pan cook steak, mushrooms and onions in hot oil until golden brown. Add bouillon, water, salt, tomato paste and mustard. Cover; simmer about 30 minutes or until tender. Combine flour and water. Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat; stir in sour cream. Heat, but do not boil. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Process softened cheese, soup and ketchup.
Combine with meat and onion.
Put in large casserole. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with biscuits and bake an additional 10 to 20 minutes, until biscuits brown.

title: halibut with celery-mustard sauce
directions: Cut halibut into serving pieces, if necessary.
Spread celery and green onions into lightly oiled baking dish.
Place halibut over mixture.
Combine chicken broth, vinegar, olive oil, mustard and paprika.
Pour over fish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes.
Remove fish to serving platter.
Stir sour cream into baking dish, combining with pan juices and vegetables.
Pour over halibut and serve.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water, sugar and salt for 5 minutes, and then cool.
Put cucumbers, garlic and dill in quart or half gallon jars.
Pour juice over them.
Refrigerate for 1 week.
Then ready to eat.

title: freda's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour and cake mix. Mix well by hand (doesn't need to be kneaded).
Let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Roll out into cinnamon rolls.
Makes two 9 x 13-inch pans or 24 rolls.
Put into pans and let rise until double in size again.
Can be put in refrigerator for up to 24 hours, or can be baked at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and ice with favorite icing.

title: fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Dip in beaten egg and water mixture.
Roll in flour mixture and fry.

title: egg rolls
directions: Soak vermicelli and fungus in warm water 15 minutes.
Then squeeze out water; finely dice.
Mix first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Scramble 1 egg in a small bowl.
Lay one lumpia wrapper on a plate and place 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons to one side of the wrapper. Roll the wrapper.
Fold end over meat and roll halfway.
Turn up each side.
Roll the rest of the way and spread the end with egg (beaten).
Deep fry until golden brown (15 minutes).
Serve with fish sauce, hot rice and lettuce.

title: country french supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 6 (16-inch) pieces of foil.
In center of each, arrange some of the potatoes and 1 chicken thigh. Season with salt and pepper.
Evenly divide carrots, green beans and onions; add to potatoes and chicken.
Sprinkle with wine, thyme and bay leaves.
Bring opposite sides of foil together and fold over twice.
Tightly fold up ends to seal.
Place packets on a large rimmed baking sheet and bake 50 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.
Cook time:
50 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Add rice, salt, pepper and cinnamon to meat and mix well.
Boil cabbage for 2 minutes after separating each leaf.
Cut the leaf into 2 pieces; stuff each with the meat and rice and roll into small firm rolls.
Arrange the rolls in a cooking pot, adding water, 1 tablespoon salt and the tomato paste; cover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed. Blend dry cake mix into hot pudding. Stir well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Scatter chocolate chips and walnuts on top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strips of beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil in a large skillet.
Stir occasionally.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cabbage, tomatoes and sauerkraut) together.
Pull leaves from cabbage; trim vein from leaves and wilt in hot water.
Make meat mixture into balls and roll in cabbage leaves.
Drain sauerkraut; place a layer in bottom of baking dish, then a layer of cabbage rolls.
Pour tomatoes over rolls; put remaining sauerkraut on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Can be cooked on stove top also.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Tear cake into chunks.
Blend sour cream and sugar; add Cool Whip and berries.
Mix with cake chunks.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add glaze on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sunset salad
directions: Add Jell-O to 1 1/2 cups of boiling water, stirring until dissolved, then add salt, juice, pineapple and carrots.
Stir until blended.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve chilled.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; mix well.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: opal's tang icebox pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, sour cream, cream cheese and Tang; pour into graham cracker pie crust. Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: pineapple bake(very popular!)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Stir in pineapple. Fold in bread cubes.
Put mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Good served with ham.

title: clam bread
directions: Cut thin layer off top of bread and remove break in chunks to use later for dipping into clam mixture.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine both sugars and sour cream in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring to 238° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are coated.
Turn onto waxed paper.
With a fork separate the nuts. Let dry.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples; place in baking dish.
Boil apple juice; add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water.
Remove apple juice from heat; stir in cornstarch paste to thicken.
Pour over apples.
Place apples in a 400° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks and mint leaves.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in oil until brown.
Remove onions; set aside.
Brown meat (add more oil, if needed).
When browned, sprinkle with flour and seasonings.
Add bouillon and wine; mix well.
Simmer on low heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Add more wine, if needed.
Return onions and add mushrooms; stir well. Simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice. Serves 8.

title: hot turkey sandwich
directions: Butter one side of bread.
Layer turkey, tomato, cheese and bacon.
Put on other slice of bread, buttered side out.
Toast on both sides.
(May use as open-faced sandwiches.)

title: skroodle salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix red beans and mixed vegetables with noodles.
Pour dressing over all; toss to coat.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken riganato
directions: Cut up chicken in
serving
pieces.
Rub
chicken
with lemon juice, then add all
other spices, olive oil and butter. Place in pan with 1 cup
of	water.	Bake
in
450° oven until golden brown.
Lower heat to 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Cook ham until tender.
Take ham out of broth.
Taste broth for saltiness.
If salty, take some broth and add water to it.
Put in broth the beans, carrots, potatoes and onion.
Cook until tender. Add some of the ham in small chunks to the soup.
(I have one meal of ham with potatoes and vegetables.
Put remaining ham in soup.)

title: oatmeal cookie pie shell
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oats, slightly crushed almonds, brown sugar and flour.
Add melted butter; toss thoroughly. Press evenly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in oven at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove from oven; press evenly with the back of a spoon.
Cool.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine the egg whites, sugar, salt, water and corn syrup in the top of double boiler.

Place over boiling water and continue beating 7 minutes or until frosting thickens and holds its shape. Remove the pan from boiling water and continue beating until thick. Frosts 24 cupcakes or 2 large 9-inch cakes.

title: grilled french bread rolls
directions: Heat olive oil in a heavy medium skillet over medium low heat. Add garlic and cook until light brown, about 4 minutes. Discard garlic. Prepare barbecue (high heat). Split rolls in half horizontally. Brush cut surfaces with garlic oil; sprinkle generously with pepper. Grill rolls, oil side down, until golden brown. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and 1 cup boiling water in deep heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add milk (if powdered or evaporated milk are used, mix with water to equal fresh milk consistency).
Simmer rice in milk, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir in eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Set in pan of hot water and bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Like all rice puddings, this one is good for any meal.
Wrapped in wax paper, cooled, it does well in a lunch bowl.
Serves 6.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put raw, crumbled hamburger in the bottom of a 13 1/2 X 8 inch dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of the hamburger meat.
Pour cream of celery on top of the cheese. Next, add the onion flakes.
Add a layer of peas, optional.
Top with tater tots.
Cover and bake at 325 degrees for at least one hour or until the meat is cooked to your liking.

title: fruit salsa and cinnamon chips
directions: In a large bowl, mix kiwis, apples, raspberries, strawberries, both sugars and fruit preserves. Cover and chill in the refrigerator at least 15 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil 2 hours in a double boiler. Serve on bun.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook in a heavy skillet until dates dissolve.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Empty 1 can coconut on wax paper and drop and roll mixture into balls coating good with the coconut.

title: yummie bars
directions: Melt stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut before completely cool.
Delicious!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly (I use my hands in plastic gloves). Shape in loaf. Spray loaf pan with vegetable oil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown.

title: nanny's chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with the milk, a little at a time. Cook and stir until thick.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue and brown in oven.
Cool and serve.

title: helen's yeast rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine, then cream in sugar.
Add egg to sugar and oleo.
Add yeast and water.
Add flour and stir.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Stir down dough.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
When they rise again and are ready, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Press crescent rolls on
a
jelly roll pan.
Brush with egg. Bake at 350° for
minutes.
Brown
meats
and drain. Add other ingredients and spread on crust and bake until brown (spread may be prepared
ahead	of
time;
warm
in
microwave before spreading on crust and bake).

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Melt together margarine and cocoa.
Cool.
Mix together sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Add to cooled butter and cocoa mixture.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately spread with Marshmallow Creme. When completely cool, frost.

title: gold cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in mixing bowl. Add Crisco and first 3/4 cup of milk called for in the recipe. Beat vigorously by hand or electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add egg yolks, additional 3/4 cup milk and lemon flavoring. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour into two 9-inch layer pans which have been greased with Crisco and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs and beat very well. Combine baking powder with cracker crumbs; add with the nuts, coconut, milk, and vanilla to creamed butter mixture.
Mix by hand until well moistened and fold into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham - cheese wedges
directions: Spread Pullman ham or luncheon meat with softened cream cheese and stack. Chill. Cut into small wedges. Spear with cocktail picks.

title: gumdrops
directions: Combine fruit pectin, water and baking soda in medium size saucepan.
(This mixture will foam.)
Combine sugar and corn syrup in large saucepan.
Place both pans over high heat.
Cook, stirring alternately, until the foam disappears from the fruit pectin mixture and the sugar mixture boils rapidly, about 5 minutes.
Pour fruit pectin mixture into the sugar mixture in a thin stream until all pectin is added.
Boil mixture, stirring constantly, 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat, stir in strawberry extract and few drops red food coloring.
Immediately pour mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: orange shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into glasses.
This is a great snack or frozen drink for kids and grown-ups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add all ingredients, stir to mix and put in casserole dish.
Top with grated sharp cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean mushrooms and save stems.
In heavy skillet, melt margarine, add green onions, celery and minced stems.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring, uncovered.
Add tomato and pepper.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Stir in the bread crumbs.
Spoon mixture into caps and arrange in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: easy mushroom rice
directions: Heat mushroom soup.
Mix together soup and cooked rice.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chips.
Pour over cereal in large bowl and mix well.
Pour powdered sugar in large brown paper sack.
Pour in cereal mixture.
Shake until well coated.
Serve in large, clean dog dish!

title: sausage eggplant jambalaya
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute chopped onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in oil until wilted.
Peel and chop eggplant and add this, plus the sausage (chopped in small pieces) to wilted vegetables.
When eggplant is well smothered, add salt and pepper to taste.
(This should be a peppery dish, so don't spare the seasoning.)
Add rice and water next.
Cover and cook Jambalaya until rice is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes over low heat.

title: italian sausage balls
directions: Allow dough to rise at room temperature for 3 hours.
Boil sausage for 15 minutes.
Cut and stretch dough into small rectangles, about 15-inches long.
After sausage cools, cut in pieces.
Dip in sauce (cold); place in middle of dough.
Fold over tightly.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° about 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 X 13-inch pan; set aside. Measure 1 cup of dry cake mix; set aside.
Combine remaining cake mix with 1 egg and oil.
Spreading mixture evenly, press into the bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine reserved cake mix, remaining 2 eggs, cream cheese, sugar, and sour cream in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes. Spread over partially baked crust.
Bake an additional 35 minutes. Cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: baked bluegills
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Gradually stir in flour, adding catsup and consomme.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sliced pickles and place fish in baking dish. Cover with sauce.
Bake at 400°
for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage soup(kapusniak-polish)
directions: Combine ham bone, the mushrooms together in liquid in which they have cooked, vegetables, sauerkraut, chopped onion and caraway seed.
Add 8 cups water and simmer until any leftover meat falls off the bone, about 1 hour.
By then about 2 cups of the liquid should have evaporated.

title: ann's pizza pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Cook ground beef (scrambled) and spread evenly in pan.
Mix tomatoes, zucchini, onions, peppers and seasoning.
Spread on top of ground beef.
Mix eggs, milk, Bisquick and 3/4 cup cheese.
Spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over top.
Bake for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip in flat dish.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread evenly over bean dip.
Add tomatoes, olives, green onion and Cheddar cheese.
Do not add picante sauce until just before serving.
Serve tortilla chips or any other type of taco-like chips.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put Crisco oil in small iron skillet; heat skillet in oven.
Mix the meal and egg in mixing bowl and stir.
Add milk and beat until well blended.
Pour into hot greased skillet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 450°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put vinegar in cup and fill with evaporated milk. Mix thoroughly and drop on a greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients. Add the egg, peanut butter, baking soda, salt and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in flour and rolled oats. Spread this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. When done baking, sprinkle the chocolate chips evenly over mixture and let stand 5 minutes. After 5 minutes, spread the chocolate chips like an icing.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Melt butter in the bottom of 8x12 inch baking dish. Stir in crushed pretzels and spread evenly in bottom of dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 min.
Cool.

title: smothered southern fried steak
directions: Season meat with seasoned salt and lemon pepper.
Roll meat in milk, then in flour.
Fry until done.
Pour tomatoes and water over steak.
Simmer over low heat until tender.
Add sugar to tomatoes.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut the chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Place in a large resealable plastic bag.
Combine egg, buttermilk and garlic powder.
Pour over chicken.
Seal and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
In another large resealable plastic bag, combine flour, bread crumbs, salt and baking powder.
Drain chicken, discarding buttermilk mixture.
Place chicken in the bag with the flour mixture; seal and shake to coat.
Fry the chicken in batches for 4 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pumpkin pie with cream cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add one egg; mix well and spread on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Combine pumpkin, 1/2 cup of sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Blend in 2 slightly beaten eggs and evaporated milk. Carefully pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until done.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Heat vinegar, egg, sugar and pineapple juice until thick. Stir continuously.
Let cool and add to remaining ingredients, stirring until thoroughly mixed.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add 3/4 package of stuffing mix and mix well to form a crust (reserve remainder to sprinkle on top).
Place cut up chicken evenly over stuffing layer and add mushrooms.
Mix together well sour cream, soup and 1 cup chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle mix on top and add remaining 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Pour boiling water over frozen broccoli and drain.
Add to cream mixture with onions and celery. Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza meat balls
directions: In a medium bowl, mix first 6 ingredients with a fork.
Shape mixture into 12 meat balls with a cube of cheese in the center of each.
On waxed paper, coat each meat ball lightly with flour.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat salad oil.
Cook meat balls until brown on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Add pizza sauce. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: catsup
directions: To the juice, add cinnamon, clove oil, sugar, vinegar and salt. Bring to boil and boil until thick, watching closely to keep from scorching.
Can while hot.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix into Bisquick. Add milk.
Knead and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Place in pan in order given. (Don't brown meat.)
Cover and bake for 5 hours at 250°.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine; press firmly on the bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: grilled cheese
directions: This makes one sandwich. Butter each slice of bread.
Place the cheese between the unbuttered sides of the bread.
Fry over medium-low heat until each side is lightly browned.
Do not place any additional oil or butter in the skillet.

title: pudding fudge
directions: Blend pudding mix with milk in saucepan.
Add butter and bring to boil.
Boil for about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, blending well.
Stir in nuts and spread in greased 4 x 8-inch pan.
Allow to cool before cutting into squares.
Makes 1 pound.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Add egg, sour milk, soda, flour, salt, bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in large loaf pan or 4 small loaves for 40 minutes.
Or 12 muffins at 25 minutes.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix sauce in pan of boiling water, brown sugar, walnuts, butter and vanilla.
Pour into baking pan.
Mix brown sugar, milk, flour, baking powder, butter and raisins.
Drop batter on sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt.
Melt butter in baking dish and add corn mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: cranberry freeze salad
directions: Soften cheese; add salad dressing and sugar.
Blend thoroughly.
Mix in fruit, nuts and whipped cream.
Pour into loaf pan and place in freezer for a minimum of 6 hours before serving. Will keep in freezer for several days.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and oleo.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour, salt, soda and spices. Blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Glaze with your favorite icing.

title: fluffy frosty
directions: Blend flour and milk in saucepan.
Heat until pasty.
Cool 1/2 hour.
Add margarine, sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
Beat at high speed approximately 5 minutes or until fluffy.

title: real banana milkshake
directions: Puree bananas in blender.
Add milk, vanilla and 1 cup ice cream.
Whip until smooth.
Add remaining ice cream and blend until thick and creamy.
Makes 2 shakes.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Add
enough
water
to	cover bottom of crock-pot.
Add sliced onion.
Salt and pepper roast and place on onion.	Add mushrooms and
pour on the soups.
Do not stir.
Cook all day on low heat or 4 to 5 hours on high.
Serve on rice or creamed potatoes.

title: mother's marble cobbler
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered dish.
Top with cherries and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cover with boiling water.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: superb ambrosia salad
directions: In large bowl, fold real mayonnaise into yogurt.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fine christmas fruit cookies
directions: Combine fruits and nuts in bowl and set aside.
Cream margarine, add brown sugar and blend.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Mix 1 tablespoon of flour mixture into the fruit and nuts.
Stir soured milk into creamed mixture, then blend in the flour mixture and vanilla.
Then add the fruit mixture.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with hardened French bread or fresh veggies.

title: rice, paella style
directions: Rub chicken, pork meat and fish with salt and oregano.
Prepare a broth using the wings, neck and bones from the meat.
Heat olive oil and saute the onions, tomatoes and peppers.
Add chicken, pork and fish; mix well and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp, clams and broth.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add rice and season to taste.
Cover and cook over low heat; when almost done (about 25 minutes) add artichokes and peas.
If possible, serve in the same pot it was cooked in.
Garnish with strips of pimento.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Work with half of the recipe at a time. Melt 1/2 stick butter in top of double boiler. Add 3/4 pound marshmallows gradually.
As they melt, there is room for more in the pot. Stir.
Pour mixture over popcorn in mixing bowl.
Alternate layers of popcorn and marshmallow mixture.
Wet hands in cold water and press into balls.

title: sauerbraten (german)
directions: Put the meat into the marinade for 3 or 4 days before cooking. Turn meat over each day so pieces are evenly saturated.
Cook on top of stove, covered, on slow heat for 2 hours in marinade. Remove bay leaves.
Can make dumplings and cook in liquid to go with Sauerbraten.
Add water, if necessary, to cook dumplings.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix tuna, onions and flour.
Add water until mixture is consistency for bread.
