Spray skillet with Pam and brown tuna patties on both sides.
Serves 2. Has 60 calories, 0 fat; food exchanges equal 3 protein, 1 bread.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine cooked chicken, Ricotta, onion, olives, parsley, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Use a teaspoon to stuff cooked shells with mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese and salsa.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Garnish with parsley and serve immediately.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in a tight container.
Use 3 to 4 tablespoons dry mix per cup.

title: mixed green salad with walnut vinaigrette
directions: In a small jar combine shallots, vinegar, walnut oil, salt and pepper.
Shake well and set aside.
Do not refrigerate.
Place greens in a salad bowl.
Toss with vinaigrette to taste and sprinkle each serving with walnuts.

title: pasta royale
directions: Heat oil, add scallions and basil; saute for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until heated through.
Toss with cooked linguine and bring to the table.
At serving time, add the shredded Mozzarella.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Mix chopped cabbage, onions and peppers.
Add sugar and salt. Let set 1 hour.
Drain off liquid.
Add the oil, vinegar and celery seed.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator bowl and cover or in a jar.
Refrigerate; keeps as long as there is any remaining.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound each chicken breast with a mallet until flat.
Wrap chicken breast around ham and cheese and secure with a toothpick. Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in butter, then in bread crumbs.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Crush crackers to fine crumbs with a rolling pin. Mix sugar and baking powder and add to crackers. Add nuts or peanut butter; mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla. Pour into 9-inch buttered, ovenproof pie plate. Bake for 25 minutes at 325°. Pie will swell. Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Use jelly roll pan.
Bring to a boil the oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Sift flour and sugar into large bowl.
Pour hot cocoa mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until it springs back.
While cake is still hot, frost.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix above ingredients well and chill.

title: cheesy quesadillas
directions: Place tortillas on baking sheet and cover with cheese. Sprinkle olives on top and top off with finely diced jalapeno peppers.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Place upon serving plates and top off with sour cream and guacamole.
Add salsa to taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut cake
directions: While cake is baking, mix sugar and evaporated milk.
Let simmer to a boil, then add grated coconut.
When cake is done, punch holes in top with a fork and pour mixture over entire cake. Spread with a spoon.
After cake cools, spread with a 13 1/2 ounce size Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top as desired.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Cut and brown hot dogs, bite size.
Cook on low heat.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: In buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, layer broccoli and cheese.
Slice butter and dot over cheese.
Put slivered almonds and chicken on top.
Refrigerate covered.
Mix can of soup, 2 tablespoons flour, 2 teaspoons milk, 1 to 2 tablespoons white wine and 1/2 cheese and sour cream.
Pour over casserole and bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Add other 1/2 cheese and sprinkle with paprika after 30 minutes. Let set 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: eggs fantastic
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Saute sausage, onion and mushrooms until cooked; drain.
Combine eggs and sour cream in blender or processor and whip for 1 minute.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender; drain thoroughly. In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender. Add soup and water and mix well. Add cheese; heat and stir until melted. Do not boil. Remove from heat. Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper. Transfer to a baking dish. In a small skillet, melt remaining butter. Cook and stir crumbs in butter until lightly browned; sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: six bean soup
directions: Soak beans by preferred method:
For each pound of dry beans, any variety, add 10 cups hot water.
May add up to 2 teaspoons of salt per pound of beans to help the beans absorb water more evenly. Heat to boiling, let boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and set aside for at least one hour, but preferably four hours or more.
The longer soaking time is recommended to allow a greater amount of sugars to dissolve, thus helping the beans to be more easily digested.
Always discard the soak water.
To maintain color integrity, soak beans separately.

title: brenda's banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Put into a greased loaf pan or muffin tin.
Bake 1 hour at 325° for bread or 25 minutes at 350° for muffins.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl. Add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth, about 1 minute. Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square baking pan in preheated hot oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.

In a medium casserole dish, layer broccoli, then the can of soup, a layer of shredded cheese, then broccoli, soup and finish off with a layer of shredded cheese. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: potato soup
directions: After preparing potatoes, onion and celery, completely cover with warm water and add salt.
Bring to boil, then turn down to simmer.
Add prepared bacon.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Turn stove off.
Add black pepper and evaporated milk.
May need to add 1 cup of regular milk.

title: baked fried chicken
directions: Mix beaten egg and milk together.
Dip chicken pieces in liquid.
Stir salt, pepper and cracker crumbs together in bowl. Dip chicken in dry mixture, using spoon to cover chicken well. Melt butter or margarine in skillet; brown breaded chicken well on both sides.
Remove browned pieces to roaster.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix together soup mix, dressing and apricot preserves.
Place chicken in Pam sprayed baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 400° for 10 minutes, reset oven to 300° and bake for 35 additional minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 layers, then split each layer when cool.

title: ginger beef
directions: Marinate steak in soy sauce, garlic, sherry or rice wine, salt, sugar, peanut oil and cornstarch.
In a wok add oil, when hot, add marinated meat and cook 1 minute, stirring briskly. Remove meat from wok to a bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to wok and when hot add salt, ginger and green onions.
Stir-fry until ginger is lightly brown.
Add soup stock or water and stir in cornstarch mixture until thickened.
Return meat to wok and stir briskly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked fish in the microwave
directions: In a square microwave pan, layer onions and potatoes (season each layer).
Lay fish on top, seasoned on both sides.
Put sliced tomatoes on fish and pour oil over all.
Cover with Saran Wrap and cook for 10 minutes on High in the microwave.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender.
Drain, then mash. Add all ingredients, except 1/2 of the butter.
Melt remaining butter.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Spread with melted butter and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On medium speed of electric mixer, beat the eggs.
Add milk and heavy cream; beat to blend.
Add butter, orange rind, sugar and 3/4 cup coconut, mixing until blended.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: On day before, brown sausage and drain.
Put bread in greased 9 x 15-inch baking dish and top with browned sausage and cheese. Mix milk and eggs.
Beat well.
Add mustard and salt.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars and egg.
Add remaining ingredients, chill. Form dough into small balls and press down with a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: elegant crab salad(a great buffet dish)
directions: Combine crabmeat, celery and onion.
Mix together remaining ingredients except lettuce and paprika.
Combine crabmeat with dressing and chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes or more.
Line salad bowl with shredded lettuce; add crabmeat mixture and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and then cube them.
Put cubed potatoes in large baking bowl.
Add diced green pepper and onion.
Cube bread into potatoes.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together.
Warm milk and margarine in small bowl in microwave.
Pour milk mixture over potatoes.
Cube the Velveeta and mix into the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles until just beginning to get tender; drain well. Saute chopped celery.
Mix noodles, meat, celery, soup and 3/4 of cheese (save some for top).
Mix well.
Place in baking dish and bake until bubbles up and hot through.

title: snow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Fold in frosting; blend well. Bake in well-greased Bundt pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Let cool. Turn onto plate. Cover with the whipped cream, topping with the shredded coconut. Keep in the refrigerator until serving.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Day ahead:
Make frosting.
Place coconuts on medium-high burner, turning for 5 minutes.
Over sink crack with hammer. Discard coconut water.
Remove and peel off brown skin.
Shred coconut in bowl.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef, onion and green pepper until the meat is no longer pink and all the vegetables are tender.
Then drain and add the next nine ingredients; mix well. Simmer, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon one-half cup mixture onto each bun.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: On a lightly greased 11 x 8-inch cookie sheet, spread crescents and pinch ends together.
Bake according to directions until very light golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread this mixture over crescent rolls.
Combine vegetables and cheese.
Sprinkle on top and press on.
Chill, cut and serve.

title: pepper nuts
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients and roll out like play dough snakes.
Cut into nuggets the size of the tip of your pinkie finger.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: pone bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and heat greased iron griddle.
Sift ingredients in bowl and cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk. Shape into 8 patties and put on hot griddle in oven.
Brown on both sides.

title: broccoli deluxe
directions: *Use fresh broccoli if desired.
Cook and drain.

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick oleo.
Add remaining ingredients; heat on low for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: sure-jell easy strawberry jam
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and corn oil and bring to a boil. Drain liquid from green beans.
Slice onions very thin.
Place beans and onions in layers in flat covered dish.
One cup of thinly sliced radishes may be added for color.
Pour hot liquid over vegetables.
When cool, cover and refrigerate.
Marinate at least 24 hours.

title: onion-pork saute
directions: Brown chops in a large frying pan or an electric skillet.
Top each with a slice of onion.
Dissolve beef broth or bouillon cube in hot water in a 1-cup measure; pour over chops.
Cover; simmer for 40 minutes, or until chops are tender.
Remove with onions and keep hot.
Sprinkle onions with paprika, if you wish.
Stir evaporated milk into drippings in pan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly hot.
Serve in separate bowl to spoon over chops.

title: chocolate ripple cake
directions: Cream the butter and gradually add sugar.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add flour, eggs and vanilla.
Measure 3 cups of batter into a greased tube pan.
Stir chocolate and flavoring into remaining batter.
Spoon chocolate mixture over batter in tube pan and, with a rubber spatula, cut and twist through batter to give a ripple effect.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out onto cooling rack.

title: amazing coconut blend pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except coconut on low speed for 3 minutes.
Grease a 9-inch pie tin.
Pour in and let set for 5 minutes.
Take coconut and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Put 1/3 sauce in long baking dish.
Layer uncooked noodles, sauce and cheese.
Put another layer of uncooked noodles.
Top with rest of sauce, cheese and ground beef.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Marinate shelled, cleaned, uncooked shrimp for 1 to 2 hours in the refrigerator in the French dressing.
Drain.
Wrap each shrimp in 1/4 slice of bacon.
Fasten with toothpick.
Broil, turning once until bacon is crisp; drain on paper towels.
May be used as an appetizer or garnish.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine
in bowl, brown sugar, oil and egg.
In another bowl, mix buttermilk, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Add both mixtures together alternately with flour;
mix well after each addition. Fold
in
apples and nuts.	Pour into muffin papers or
greased muffin
pans
and
sprinkle sugar, oleo and spice mixture over top.
Bake	at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 15 muffins.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
ingredients in order as written.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: mint chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar, mint and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Combine baking soda, flour and salt.
Gradually beat the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture. Stir in chips (and nuts, if using).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly and remove from the cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: my mom's lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all and pour into graham cracker pie crust.

title: lemon mustard chicken(makes 2 servings)
directions: On flat plate, blend flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour, shaking off excess.
Heat oil over medium-high heat and saute chicken until golden brown on both sides and cooked through. Transfer to plate and keep warm in oven.
Add broth to pan to deglaze 2 to 3 minutes.
Add pepper and green onions; cook 2 minutes.

title: hot chicken or turkey sandwich
directions: Make a sauce of stock, milk, flour and butter.
Add next 3 ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Place on slices of toast and serve.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna(excellent)
directions: Brown first 8 ingredients.
When brown, add tomato sauce and mashed tomatoes.
Simmer.
Cook lasagna noodles (add oil to the water).
Sequence in pan: sauce, layer of noodles, grated cheese and pizza cheese.
Keep repeating until all noodles are gone.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt bark, then stir in remaining ingredients. Drop on wax paper to cool. Store in air tight container.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt Crisco or oil.
Chop medium large onions and add to oil.
Saute until transparent.
Add paprika. Makes a bright red color.
Add chicken pieces with parsley to really cover chicken.
Let stew 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and place in bowl.
To juices of meat, add milk and flour.
Mix well. Add the chicken back and cook on low for 5 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes, egg noodles or rice.

title: texas cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and heat until dissolved.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add hot mixture.
Pour on greased and floured cookie sheet, 18 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to a boil.
Add butter and peanuts. Cook to a hard crack stage.
Turn off heat before adding soda; stir in soda and mix well.
Pour in a buttered pan and shake.

title: mozzarella salad
directions: Cut Mozzarella into thin strips.
Slice tomatoes into thin wedges.
Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices and drop in boiling water for 2 minutes; drain and cool under running water.
Combine all ingredients and toss.
Let chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook hamburg; drain and keep grease.
Add onion and pepper to grease; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and bean sprouts.
Heat until hot.
Add to cooked macaroni.

title: bean soup
directions: Cover
beans with water.
Add first 4 ingredients. Cook bacon until
crisp, remove bacon; reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon
and set
aside.
Add
onions and green pepper to drippings.
Saute until
tender.
Add
onion,
green
pepper
and carrots
to beans. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour. Add
tomato
sauce. Cover and simmer an additional 30 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle bacon over soup when served.

title: vegetable fajita
directions: In a medium to large frypan, melt pat of butter or spray butter to coat pan.
Add about 1/3 to 1/2 cup of water.
Add more if necessary.
Prepare your favorite vegetables, chopped or cut up, and add to water in frypan.
Simmer about 10 minutes or until done to your desired texture.
On a microwave-safe plate, place a flour tortilla.
Top with about 1 to 2 tablespoons of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Warm in microwave about 35 seconds until melted on the edges.
Put desired amount of vegetables in the middle and turn right edge over filling, then left side.
It's ready to eat.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine in a big roaster and cook at 225° for 6 hours or until done.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat together cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups sugar,
eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust and cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: junk cake
directions: Put pie filling on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then pour pineapple on top of that, juice and all.
Pour dry cake mix on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top of dry cake mix. Pour butter over top of that and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Bring to a boil, vinegar, sugar and oil.
Pour over vegetables, add onions, celery and peppers.
Chill for 4 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let frozen bread dough thaw and rise according to package directions.
Spread out in large rectangle (approximately 10 x 12-inch).
Brush with mixture of beaten egg, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Top with layer of pepperoni and cheese.
Fold over; layer again and fold over.
Seal all edges.
Brush top with egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Serve hot, sliced in 1-inch slices.
Wrapped in foil, bread will freeze well.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Place chicken in 2 1/2 cups of water with 2 teaspoons of salt in a large saucepan.
Cook until tender.
Reserve broth and cube chicken.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Divide dough into 45 balls.
Press into miniature muffin tins. Bake until done.
As soon as you take the cookies out of the oven, place a Reese's cup into center.
Be sure and let cool completely before you take out or they will crumble.

title: low calorie dessert
directions: Bring to a boil the crushed pineapple (with its juice). Dissolve jello in this.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip and mix with electric mixer.
Chill.

title: chicken waldorf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Wash and remove stems from mushrooms. Brown sausage.
Drain sausage and mix with softened cream cheese. Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel, half and remove egg cores.
Mix the yolks and next 3 ingredients and spoon into egg halves.
Top with paprika.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Heat the chicken broth in a saucepan.
Add onion and celery. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add asparagus and simmer for 20 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper if needed.
Discard the onion.
Mix the flour and paprika in a small bowl and blend in enough cold water to form a smooth paste.
Stir in the sour cream.
Whisk this mixture into the hot soup.
Return just to simmering point and let bubble slightly for 10 minutes to cook the flour.
Do not let soup boil or the sour cream will curdle.
Cauliflower can be substituted for asparagus.

title: graham cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and canned milk; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add to mixture the graham crackers, coconut and marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Spoon onto wax paper; let set until firm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, melted oleo and 1 egg.
Spread in well-greased 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 4x sugar and 2 eggs. Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: tired mom's cake
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In layers spread crushed pineapple, then cherry pie filling on top of that. Next sprinkle dry cake mix out of box over cherries.
Spread melted butter evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle coconut and pecans on top of cake.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: steak stripes ol
directions: Cut steak diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch thick strips. Thread beef evenly onto 36 (6-inch) wooden skewers, weaving back and forth. Place in a shallow dish. Combine lime juice and remaining 6 ingredients. Pour over beef. Cover and chill 30 minutes. Preheat the grill. Cook beef, without grill lid, over medium coals (300° to 350°) 3 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness. Garnish with lime curls, if desired. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Season to taste.
Add second pie crust to top pie.
Make slits.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
(You can use turkey or ham.)

title: tangy grilled sirloin
directions: Use the last 2 ingredients if you like it hot.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Defrost shrimp.
Mix tomato soup, cream cheese and water together over low heat.
When smooth, add gelatin and stir.
Remove from heat.
When cooled, add mayonnaise.
Mix onion, celery and pepper and add to sauce.
Fold in shrimp.
Pour into greased 6-cup mold and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: If nuts are omitted, use 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, put eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and salt.
To the flour, add the baking soda, baking powder and add to the liquid mixture.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
Pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Margarine, eggs and whipping cream need to be at room temperature.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread; put in a pan or mixing bowl.
Melt margarine; pour over crumbs.
Beat eggs, 2 cups milk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla; pour over bread crumbs.
Heat remaining milk and sugar to scalding point; pour over bread mixture.
Mix in the cinnamon. Mix together good with spoon or with hands real good.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam at 350° for 1 hour, or until it sets.
When done, take out and let set until cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium bowl, combine baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken to serve 45
directions: Cook hens until tender enough to come off the bones in 2 quarts or more of liquid.
Make custard of 2 quarts of broth and remaining ingredients (except dressing).
Cook until custard consistency.

title: italian potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel and mash with potato masher. Put in large bowl and add salt, pepper, garlic powder, parsley, Parmesan cheese, diced ham, eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix by hand and put in a casserole dish that has been greased with butter or margarine.
Put pats of butter or margarine on top and sprinkle with the Italian bread crumbs.
Bake for about 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Cut ham into cubes, brown lightly in skillet.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Heat milk
to a boiling point, then add salt, pepper, ham and potatoes.
Put
into
a 2 quart casserole dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all four ingredients until well mixed.
Add dressing and mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Keep refrigerated.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Serve at once.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: Blend milk, egg beaters, sugar, vanilla, and cinnamon, and then set aside.
Place bread cubes into a lightly grease 8x8 baking dish.
Sprinkle
with the blueberries.
Pour over the egg mixture.
Set dish in a pan filled with 1 inch of hot water and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until set.
Serve with warm caramel sauce.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Dot with butter.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jeanne's taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 inch pie plate or square casserole dish.
Cook beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Place in pie plate of dish and sprinkle chillie peppers on top.
In separate bowl,
beat milk, eggs, and Bisquick until smooth. Pour over meat. Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake until knife comes out clean when inserted, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, lettuce, extra tomatoes, and cheese if desired.
Great as leftovers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add taco seasoning and water and simmer about 15 minutes.
Place in a large bowl and chill.
Add onion, mayonnaise and cheese, mixing gently.
Toss in tomato, lettuce and chips that have been coarsely crushed.
Sprinkle with olives and top with salsa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip each biscuit into melted butter.
Coat with cinnamon mixture.
Place in pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Remove from oven; loosen rolls immediately.
Yields 10 rolls.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Blend well.
Add eggs and beat. Blend in bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in hot water. Add the cheese.
When jello cools, refrigerate until mixture is slushy.
Add the pineapple and mayonnaise.

title: fast and fabulous fruit
directions: Combine pudding mix and fruit with juice in bowl.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Garnish as desired.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and put spaghetti in.
Mix egg and milk in bowl; add to spaghetti. Mix well and spread over bottom of pan.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in 1/2 cup water; let cool, then add last.
Pour all ingredients in greased pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rumaki
directions: Drain chestnuts.
Add soy sauce to can of drained chestnuts. Marinate for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Wrap chestnuts in bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Sprinkle with brown sugar; broil until bacon is crisp.

title: favorite chilli(crock-pot)
directions: Put in crock-pot in order.
Stir once.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours; high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: beef and green pepper
directions: Cut beef in long strips and sprinkle with soy sauce.
Leave them 7 to 8 minutes; add cornstarch.
Cook beef in oil, a small quantity at a time.
Put aside.
Cook green pepper first in oil and bamboo sprouts next.
Add salt.
When green pepper becomes tender, add Sake, soy sauce, sugar and Accent, then return the meat to the pan.

title: waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron to medium heat. Drop eggs into bowl. Add milk and mix until blended. Put butter in a small saucepan and melt over low heat.
Be careful not to let butter burn. Stir butter into the egg mixture.
Presift the flour, then sift measured flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour a little butter on waffle iron.
Pour batter onto iron and cook. Serves 6 waffles.

title: peanut butter crunch balls
directions: Mix ingredients except chocolate.
Chill for 1 hour.
Make small balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Put on waxed paper to harden.

title: mom's apricot bread
directions: Soak and grind dried apricots.
Mix together sugar, butter and eggs.
Add water and orange juice.
Sift and add to the mixture, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Pour into one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, tomatoes, bread, egg, onion, salt, pepper and sugar.
Place in baking dish in form of loaf and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off excess fat. Pour tomato soup (and a little water from rinsing the can) over meat loaf and continue baking 25 minutes more.

title: sliced baked potato
directions: Bring to boil in large pot of salted water 2 (10 ounce) packages frozen mustard greens or 2 large bunches of fresh, washed 3 to 4 times to remove sand.
Fresh greens will decrease in size as they cook.
Frozen and fresh should cook 30 to 40 minutes. Drain all water off.
Use 4 packets of MBT (chicken flavor); mix well.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put oranges, apples and cranberries through food chopper.
Add sugar, mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: tuna dip
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix; store in airtight bowl.
May be unmolded on a bed of lettuce for fancy dip tray.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage crescent rolls
directions: Filling:
Brown sausage. Add onion before all the pink is gone in the sausage.
Drain. Put back into the pan and add the mushrooms and cream cheese.
Stir together and chill.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Form into walnut size balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: audrey's surprise dessert
directions: Crust the crackers; melt the margarine.
Remove from heat. Add the sugar.
Stir in the cracker crumbs.
Press 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine and peanut butter until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, except kisses.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes in an ungreased pan.
While hot, press chocolate kisses in center.

title: seven minute chicken
directions: Mix together cheese, bread crumbs and wheat germ.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and then in cheese mixture.
Arrange in one layer in microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Rotate 1/4 turn and cook additional 3 minutes on High.

title: yaki-mish (japanese)
directions: Brown meat on medium-high heat setting, stirring often.
Add vegetables and cook 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and rice.
Stir and mix well but lightly.
Taste before salting, because soy sauce is salty.
Good served with a green salad and French bread.
Yields 6 servings.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix all together.
Beat egg whites and stir in last.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° until done.

title: easy  lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add onions, cook until tender.

Stir in tomato sauce and basil. Simmer 10 minutes.	Prepare dinner as directed on package. Spread half the dinner into greased dish. Top with meat mixture, 1/2 cup parmesan cheese and remaining dinner. Melt margarine in sauce pan over low heat.	Blend in flour. Gradually add milk.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened. Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs.
Return to hot mixture.
Pour over all. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: laurie's cheesecake
directions: To make crust:
Use your own favorite graham cracker crumb recipe or try this.
Combine the first three ingredients listed in a spring-form pan to form crust.
(I use a 9 or 10-inch pan). Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: texas chili
directions: In large pot, brown beef and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Great served over baked potatoes.

title: homestyle chicken-noodle soup
directions: In a 4-quart casserole dish, arrange chicken with bony pieces in center and meaty pieces to outer edges.
Add water; stir in onion, celery, carrot, chicken bouillon and poultry seasoning.
Tie peppercorns in cheesecloth and add soup.
Cover; microwave on High for 20 minutes or until boiling.
Then microwave on Medium-low for 15 minutes.
Rearrange chicken and add noodles.
Cover and microwave at Medium-low for 30 minutes until noodles are tender, stirring several times and give dish a 1/2 turn once.
Remove chicken pieces and peppercorns from soup.
Skim excess fat from soup.
Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Discard bones and skin. Cut up chicken and return 1 1/2 cups.
Refrigerate remaining chicken for another use.
Microwave soup on High for 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: joe's roast beef and potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into 1-inch long strips.
Melt butter in black frypan.
Add potatoes; coat with butter.
Bake until tender, turning several times, at 350°.
When potatoes are light brown, add roast beef and stir lightly.
Cook about 15 minutes, until beef is hot.

title: microwave pie crust
directions: Melt margarine in pie plate in microwave.
Mix other ingredients with melted butter and press in pan with fingers to shape crust.
Ready for use.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix together until smooth and pour over cake.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream 1/2 cup butter with brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour.
Press in a 9-inch square pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Spread pineapple on top of this.
Beat together 1/4 cup butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and coconut.
Spread over pineapple and return to oven for additional 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding and mix well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat, layering twice, ending with pudding.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: fruit saladdallas, texas
directions: Peel and slice bananas and apples and sprinkle with lemon juice so they don't turn brown.

title: cheesy onion soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, salt, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickens.
Add shredded cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and line with bread slices (crusts cut off).
In blender, combine eggs and milk.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Melt butter and drizzle over top. Add crumbled bacon, sausage or ham (if desired).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: basic italian sauce(with meat)
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil.
Add garlic and sliced onion and saute.
Add tomato puree plus 1 can of water, tomato paste and 1 can of water.
Mix. Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle in all spices, cheese, Angostura Bitters and Worcestershire.
Stir all together. Brown the sausage and meatballs (see recipes in meat section).
Add to the sauce.
Allow to simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, or until sauce is slightly thickened and meat is cooked.
Add more of spices, if needed.
May be doubled or tripled.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Pour washed elderberries into unbaked
pie
crust.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the
berries.
Cover
with top crust. Bake at 425° for 10
minutes,
then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: easter bread
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Mix butter, eggs, sugar and flour. Add milk.
Mix soft dough.
Let rise to double in size, then punch down and shape into round loaves.
Let rise for about 40 minutes. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with rye bread.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg, butter and eggs. Beat until smooth. Pour over rhubarb in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix cabbage and green onions.
Refrigerate.
Saute butter, noodles, almonds and sesame seeds.
Saute chicken breasts separately in butter and soy sauce.
Add to listed ingredients sauce after chopping.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 20 minutes before serving. Stays good for several days.

title: layered crab dip
directions: Completely cover the bottom of a flat-bottomed serving dish (similar to a pie plate) with the cream cheese.
This is the bottom layer of the dip.
Next, completely cover cream cheese with crabmeat.
The final layer is to cover the crabmeat with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers or thinly sliced toasted French bread.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine together and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix 2 remaining eggs, sugar and cream cheese together and pour on top of first layer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When cool, cut into squares.

title: pot roast(chuck, round or brisket)
directions: In chicken fryer or heavy roaster, brown meat in hot oil. Add onion until golden brown. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat. May add potato and carrot wedges. Veggies may be precooked in the microwave.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, until well blended.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: squash delight casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender (in water).
Drain; add margarine and mash.
Mix sugar, egg, mayonnaise, pepper, onion, salt and cheese.

title: bonbons
directions: In saucepan, melt peanut butter and oleo.
In large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut mixture over cereal.
Blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls. Chill to form.
Melt butterscotch or chocolate pieces separate in double boiler.
Dip balls in coating, swirling with back of spoon. Place on wax paper lined baking sheet and chill.

title: oriental cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cranberry orange relish, ginger, water chestnuts and celery seed.
Pour into molds. Chill until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Sift flour, then measure.
Add soda and sift again.
Mix all together and bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: "party punch"
directions: Mix hot water, jello and sugar together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Add ginger ale when you are ready to serve.
(Make sure ginger ale is cold.)

title: orange marmalade(microwave)
directions: Blend equal parts of flour and butter.
Roll into small balls. Drop in as many as needed to thicken as desired.
No lumps!

title: dad's casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onions until it changes color; mix in cottage cheese and set aside.
Cook noodles until half tender; drain.
Put noodles and hamburger in layers in casserole starting and ending with noodles.
Mix soup and milk; pour over mixture. Beat egg and pour over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: rebel rolls
directions: Slice the cream cheese put on one side of the cutlets. Then add jal. on top. Roll up and wrap in bacon. Stick with toothpick. Great to bbq.

title: fruit in a cone
directions: Dip top of cone into melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with sprinkles.
Put cut-up fruit in cone.
Drizzle with honey. Sprinkle with granola.

title: shrimp with wild rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions (about 1 hour). Makes 4 cups cooked rice.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: *After measuring oatmeal, put a small amount, about 1 cup, into a blender until it turns into powder.

title: 4th of july on observation hill
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes and gravy mix.
Using 2 1/2 or 3 qt casserole, combine meat mixture with beans.
Cut onions into thick slices.
Put a few cloves into casserole and add in brown sugar. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Pour all ingredients in bowl except graham cracker crumbs. Mix until smooth.
Form into small balls and roll in the graham cracker crumbs.

title: foccacio bread
directions: Combine salt, flour and rosemary.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Combine the wet mixture with the dry (salt, flour, rosemary) mixture using a spatula.
Stir until evenly moist and beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Cover for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend pudding mix in milk with wire whisk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of whipped topping, mixing well. Set aside.
In large deep glass bowl alternate cookies, bananas and pudding mixture in layers.
Top with reserved whipped topping and additional banana slices if desired.
Refrigerate overnight. Yield 16 servings.
This recipe can be made using 1/3 or 2/3 measures.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook sausage until brown and drain.
Melt cheese in microwave. Stir every minute.
Add sausage and picante sauce.
Keep hot in small crock-pot.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix the first five ingredients (margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla) together.
Mix well.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill for at least one hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick and cut to desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased sheet for 7 to 9 minutes.
After cooled, frost with icing.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Prepare stuffing; then put in pie plate to make a layer.
Add can corn, drained.
brown hamburger and onion.
Drain; put on top of corn.
Sprinkle seasoning.
Layer mashed potatoes on top of hamburger.
Put soup on top of potatoes.
Microwave 10 to 15 minutes or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll dough to an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cover dough with meat and cheese.
Roll up lengthwise and seal ends and edges.
Let rise again until almost double.
Brush with beaten egg, parsley and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Place loaf seam side down on greased cookie sheet.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream well the sugar and eggs.
Slowly add oil and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add milk gradually, with Pet milk, poppy seed and nuts.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Stays moist 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and make in long molding rolls and let stand (preferably overnight).
Put in icebox until morning.
Slice into thin slices and bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine oil and sugar, beat until smooth.
Add 4 egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients, which have been sifted together. Stir in potatoes, pecans and vanilla; beat well.
Beat 7 egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Fold in sugar.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
While mixing, preheat oven to 375°.
Put cookies in oven and turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open until next day.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Bring 1 cup of water to boil in saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Meanwhile, cook egg in butter in a 10-inch skillet until set.
Add scallions and rice; cook and stir over medium heat until rice and scallions are lightly browned. Combine remaining water and soy sauce.
Stir mixture into rice.

title: ma's homemade soup
directions: Fill a large pot with 1 gallon of water.
Add soup bones and stewed tomatoes with salt and pepper.
When meat is cooked, remove bones.
Dice potatoes and add to pot.
Cook 5 minutes after liquid starts to boil; then drain liquid off the mixed vegetables.
Add to pot; bring to a boil and cook 5 more minutes.
Then add macaroni to pot; cook until tender.
Just before serving, add a can of cream-style corn, stirring well.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place balls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8-9 minutes or until set.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: lime sherbet molded salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sherbet until well blended.
Cool until syrupy. Spoon whipped topping into a large mixing bowl.
Gradually beat in the gelatin mixture on low speed until well blended.
Pour into 12 c. mold coated with nonstick spray.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until hot, about 30 minutes.

title: goolosh
directions: Peel and cube potatoes (large cubes).
Boil in salt water until tender.
Brown ground beef; season to your taste.
(I like to use salt, pepper, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce and sometimes cayenne pepper.)
Drain beef and add onions, cooking until onions are tender.
Add potatoes and enough of the water to make soupy.
Mix all together and season again if needed.

title: chili rio grande
directions: After cooking bacon in a heavy skillet, saute onions until golden.
Mix in cumin, oregano, red pepper, Tabasco, paprika, cayenne, chili powder, salt and garlic.
Stir in kidney beans and tomatoes.
Simmer slowly, stirring, for 1/2 hour.
Mix in ground beef and simmer 10 minutes.
Thin with bouillon, if necessary. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk cut-outs
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Alternate adding buttermilk and flour.
Chill 24 hours.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes (roll thick).
These cookies are meant to be soft.

title: spinach salad supreme
directions: Crumble bacon. Drain again on absorbent paper.
In a small bowl or glass jar, combine bacon drippings, olive oil and vinegar. Mix well. Set aside.

title: mints
directions: Mix with hands.
Will be stiff.
Pinch off small amount and roll in hands. Press in mold.
Can make 3 or 4 days before using. Also can freeze.
Yields 100 mints.

title: death chili
directions: Into bowl, place "thick" hot sauce, 2 tablespoons cayenne, 2 tablespoons garlic powder, 2 tablespoons chili powder, brown sugar and ground beef mixed together until thoroughly even.
For an interesting addition, 1/2 cup white wine can be mixed in to increase the heat.

Place onion, celery, green pepper, chopped jalapenos, 2 tablespoons Tabasco sauce, 2 tablespoons chili powder, butter and 2 tablespoons cayenne into saucepan and saute until all are softened or slightly browned.
In a high-walled skillet, brown hamburger mixture.
Combine the sauteed vegetables and add the beans (undrained), tomatoes (undrained), bay leaf and tomato paste.
Add any remaining ingredients you may have at this time and cook on a medium flame, slowly stirring until 5 minutes after it has come to a boil.
Remove bay leaf and serve with pitchers of water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
While hot, add cranberries. Mix until cranberry liquid has dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add celery, nuts and pineapple.
Pour in 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch dish.

title: clarissa roddy's war cake
directions: Note:
Made during the war when milk, eggs and butter were all rationed.

title: "galopeta" - custard dessert
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk and sugar over a low flame.
Add the sifted cake flour gradually and stirring constantly.
Add the butter and continue stirring until thickened.
Have the eggs well beaten.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl place confectioners sugar, 2 eggs, 2 sticks oleo and vanilla.
Beat 20 minutes with electric beater (do not underbeat).
Spread thin over crumbs.
Spread 2 cups well-drained pineapple over this.
Cut in thirds lengthwise 4 or more bananas.
Layer close together over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Top with chopped walnuts and cherries. Chill and serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients at one time.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This can also be made with other fruit.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Shape into patties and fry. When done, top with soup and simmer.

title: no-bake chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Mix milk, butter, sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Mix well and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil exactly 3 minutes then remove from heat and immediately add peanut butter, salt and vanilla. Gradually add oats and mix well.
Spread on greased sheet pan 1/2-inch thick and cut into squares when cool.
Makes 25 squares.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix together flour, 3 tablespoons margarine, salt and sugar.
Heat to a paste 5 minutes, then add onion, sour cream and cheese.
Top with cornflakes mixed with remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in blender; blend for 10 seconds at a time 3 to
4 times.
Pour into buttered, floured 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
You can sprinkle with cinnamon before baking.
Add 1 cup of coconut, if desired.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening with mixer.
Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape bottom and sides of bowl often.
When all the sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Frosts 3 layers or 9 x 12-inch cake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place chopped onion into 3 cups of water in a large saucepan; cook until quite tender.
Add chopped broccoli, adding just enough water to completely cover broccoli.
Continue cooking for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Alternate flour, cocoa mixture and buttermilk to mixture.
Beat well. Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Add to batter. Add salt, vanilla and food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy onion stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Remove stems from mushrooms; discard stems.
Fill caps with whipped cream cheese and broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: collards
directions: Wash collard leaves 4 or 5 times in fresh water.
(Twist leaves into or cut in strips.)
In an iron pot, bring water to a boil, drop in leaves and boil to shrink.
Add neck bones and salt, cook until tender.
May have to add more water.
Cook slow for a long time.
(Add 1 whole pecan in hull to prevent strong odor.)

title: western beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, mix all ingredients and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat and stir soup, cream cheese till well mixed. Put 3/4 pkg. of potatoes in buttered casserole dish. Pour and mix in soup and cheese mixture. Sprinkle cheddar cheese over top and bake.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.

Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and add oatmeal and chopped nuts. Shape into rolls and roll into wax paper; cool in refrigerator. Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased cookie sheets for about 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with no-stick cooking spray. Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add combined milk, egg whites, honey and oil; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Mix cherry Jell-O; put in bottom of serving bowl.
Let chill. Mix cream cheese with a little milk and put over cherry Jell-O when chilled.
Mix lime Jell-O with pineapple and pour over salad.

title: corn-lima bean casserole
directions: Cook
corn
and
lima
beans as package directs, adding green onion
tops
so
that all vegetables are cooked, but not overdone. Drain.
Set
aside.

of the margarine in a 2 quart pan over medium heat.
Blend in flour. Add

Cook until thick. Simmer 2
or 3 minutes.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and pimento. Combine
sauce with cooked and drained vegetables.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Drizzle with remaining
