of margarine which has been melted.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Time of preparation: 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix like pie dough.
Chill 2 hours and roll out like pie dough.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch or 2-inch squares or diamond shapes. Fill with any filling.
Fold over and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: a meal in one dish
directions: Cook pasta shells according to directions on package.
Saute ground beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Place beef in three-quart casserole.
Saute onion; add soup, milk, peas and oregano.
Add to beef in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil using a heavy kettle.
Cook until
the mixture begins to change color.
Add peanuts immediately.
Continue to cook until light amber (Peanut Brittle color).
Peanuts will clump together so keep stirring apart.
Remove from heat immediately and add butter, soda and salt.
Stir in rapidly.
Spread on a well-buttered cookie sheet, pushing the peanuts down into the candy and also spreading it to the thinness you desire.
Cool and break up.

title: pinto bean and feta cheese quesadillas
directions: Process first six ingredients. Using on/off turns of processor until a very chunky puree forms.
Transfer to bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
(Can be prepared day ahead. Cover and chill.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In 3 cups reserved chicken stock add onions, tomatoes and garlic.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add the spaghetti and cook another 12 minutes or until spaghetti is done.
Mix in cheese, mushrooms, seasonings and cut up chicken.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and bake.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and flour.
Add eggs and beat well. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and put in two pie shells. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: elmer's baked beans
directions: Soak
beans
overnight in cold water.
Bring beans to a boil and
cook
until
the
skin on the beans rolls back when blown on. Cut bacon into small pieces.
Drain beans (save the liquid). Layer beans, brown sugar and bacon in a large baking dish or casserole.
Bake at 300° for 4 to 6 hours, until beans are
brown and
soft
in
texture.
Stir
occasionally
while baking.
Add retained
liquid from beans as desired, to maintain preferred consistency and prevent overbrowning.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix oleo and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Arrange meat on kraut.
Spoon on Thousand Island dressing.
Place cheese slices on meat.
Sprinkle on bread cubes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef and drain. Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: *date and nut cake
directions: Mix together floured dates, baking soda and boiling water; let cool.
Mix separately margarine or butter, sugar and egg.
To this mixture, add flour, salt, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Lastly, add date mixture.
Place in greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When baked and cooled, place in plastic bag and allow to age for 3 weeks in the refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Bake in buttered pan at 325° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: tuna pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and oregano.
Spread on sliced open French rolls, or French bread sliced lengthwise. Sprinkle cheese and oregano on top.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with jello salad.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients with milk.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook without stirring, until it reaches soft ball stage or 238° on candy thermometer.
Do not scrape sides on pan.
Add dates and nuts.
Cook until forms a firm ball in water or 250° on candy thermometer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat as fudge.
When mixture begins to thicken, pour onto damp cloth and roll.
Let stand 24 hours before slicing.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: trash
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large roasting pan. Stir in seasoning salt and Worcestershire.
Mix in cereal, nuts and pretzels until well coated.
Bake 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, building up a 1/2-inch ledge.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat the remaining ingredients about 3 minutes, until light and fluffy. Pour over hot crust.
Bake about 25 minutes longer, or just until no imprint remains when touched lightly in center.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: fast coffee cake
directions: Layer in order into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Dot with butter; cover and leave on the counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in large heavy skillet or Dutch oven. Add beef, onion and green pepper. Cook over medium heat until meat browns lightly. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms and seasonings. Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. (I usually cook mine longer, about an hour on low.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat, add onion, peppers and cheese.
Mix together corn meal, eggs, buttermilk, salt, soda, oil and corn.
Put 1/2 of meal mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour all of meat mixture over it.
Spread rest of meal mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer in order.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl with mixer.
Pour in ice cream freezer and finish with milk.

title: split pea with ham soup
directions: Rinse peas.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bone; cut off ham meat and dice.
(If no bone, add 1 cup diced ham to soup.)

title: red devils food cake
directions: Sift last 4 ingredients together.
Mix eggs, sugar, milk and coffee well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and vanilla.
Bake in sheet pan or layer pans.
You may use sour half and half in place of sour milk (richer).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. This is a Piwetz favorite for 44 years.

title: microwave peach jam
directions: Mash peaches; combine with all ingredients in deep 2 quart casserole.
Cover; microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir and cover; microwave 3 to 4 minutes or until boils for 1 minute.
Remove. Stir 2 minutes.
Pour into freezer container.
Cover and freeze. Thaw to serve.
Store in freezer up to 1 year; in refrigerator 1 month.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Beat in yolk of an egg.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Freeze firmly.
Roll into crust.

title: white chip orange cookies(makes 3 dozen.)
directions: Combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat the butter and sugars in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg and orange rind. Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make an ice ring of 7-Up.
If punch bowl is large enough, you can double the recipe.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter.
Gradually add flour and knead like biscuit dough.
Separate in sections; roll out on floured surface.
Cut with cutter for cookies.
May have to add a little milk to help thin dough down, or a little more flour, whichever is needed.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until slightly brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Shake before serving.
Makes 1 pint.

title: muffins
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Combine all ingredients well.
Bake in oven preheated to 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and dust with powdered sugar. Makes 75 small muffins.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix in bowl Cheez Whiz and cream cheese until soft.
Add garlic powder or garlic salt to taste.
Spread on hot bread.

title: lena's sunday breakfast baked eggs
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan with Pam.
Cut a hole in the center of each slice of bread using a glass.
Place in pan.
Break eggs, one at a time, over each hole in the bread.
Top with 1 slice of American cheese on each.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: easy sandwiches
directions: Cook arm roast on low overnight in crock pot.
Freeze broth. Tear up roast.
Add bottle of Country Bob's, mushrooms and green pepper.
Buy package of steak buns.
Add mixture to buns and add cheese and eat.

title: chili bean soup
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery.
Saute ground beef and drain fat.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake in greased Bundt pan.

title: mother's pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a pastry blender or
2 knives, cut together the flour, salt and shortening.
For best results, ingredients should be very cold.
Form a ball.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately with water to sugar mix. Pour into two well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: under-the-sea salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving 3/4 cup of the syrup. Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add syrup and lemon juice.
Measure 1 1/4 cups into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or a 4-cup mold.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 1 hour.

title: whole wheat apple raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, raisins, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Peel the potatoes and then cut them into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Then combine the rest of the ingredients together in a 7 x 7-inch casserole dish and add the potato slices.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes at 375°.
Then remove the cover and bake for another 15 minutes at 375°.
Then remove the cover and bake for another 15 minutes.
This is all there is to this great dish. Watch out . . .
those potatoes stay hot for a long time!
Serves 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook and stir last 4 ingredients until clear.
When clear, add beets and place pan, covered, over hot water for 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, heat beets again and add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: excellent custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell in glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Dice and fry onion in butter until tender.
Add paprika and stir well.
Add chicken wings and vegetables.
Add 5 quarts water and a 13 1/2 ounce can of chicken broth.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Bring to a boil and add noodles.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup of the margarine and all the crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole. Combine the margarine and crumbs; spread over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed tex-mex peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Discard seeds and membranes. On a 12-inch microwave-safe plate, arrange peppers, cut side down. Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap; turn back one corner to vent steam.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Invert pepper halves over paper towels.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix all together, adding carrots.
After all is mixed thoroughly, marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold. Carrots keep about 1 week in the refrigerator.

title: hot chili(alabama style)
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet. When meat is done, place in a colander and run hot water over it to remove excess fat. Make sure it is well done. Add all ingredients together in a large pot or slow cooker. Cook until onions are tender. The chili is done at this time but will taste better if it's allowed to slow cook for about 3 hours. Stir occasionally to make sure all seasoning is well blended.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Sauce:
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic powder and ground ginger.

title: frosted green salad
directions: In large salad bowl, add ingredients in order.
Frost with mayonnaise (thick).
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, cover with sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Crumble bacon bits and croutons over top.

title: divinity candy
directions: Beat egg whites real stiff.
Cook sugar, syrup and water to medium soft ball.
Pour 1/2 syrup over beaten egg whites.
Continue beating.
Cook remaining syrup to hard crack stage, then pour over candy and continue beating until it starts to get real thick.
Take beater out and beat with spoon.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until stands up.
Put out on greased paper by spoonfuls.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 2/3 stick margarine in each of two 9-inch (nonstick coated) round cake pans.
Stir 7/8 cup brown sugar in each.

title: sweet 'n' sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with onion, milk and egg.
Make meatballs, the size of golf balls.
Bake meatballs in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 375°.
Drain off fat.

title: ham and potato stew
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut in 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick slices.
Halve or quarter slices if you prefer.
Put in saucepan, add just enough water to cover.
Cook 10 minutes; add onion slices, ham and parsley.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add a small amount of water if necessary while the stew is cooking.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Saute onions in oil, add ground meat and brown well.
Add tomatoes, water, rice, chili powder, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Remove tops and seeds from the peppers and parboil for 5 minutes; drain.
Stuff the peppers with the onion/meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in greased baking dish, add small amount of water.
Top each pepper with bread crumbs, if desired.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread into a plate container or pizza pan.
Refrigerate overnight. Top with tomatoes, onions, black olives and cheese.

title: jim's curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serves many; good with fresh vegetables, fruit, shrimp, chips and/or crackers.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Mix together.
Add cheese and dressing.
Crush Doritos and add.
Slice avocado and add. Brown the ground beef; drain.
Drain beans; add to meat.
Add salt; simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine with cold salad.

title: betty's salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; finish filling cup with water and heat. Dissolve Jell-O in heated juice.
Cool.
Add chopped apple (unpeeled), few grains of salt, milk, mashed cream cheese, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Add approximately 1/4 cup orange juice.
Mold.

title: chicken-stuffed dumplings
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and 2 tablespoons onion with 1 1/4 cups water in large skillet, mixing well.
Bring to a simmer. Combine 2 tablespoons onion and remaining ingredients (except biscuits), mixing well.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream cake mix and cream cheese. Add eggs, oil and water. Dust blueberries with flour and fold in. Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Boil Jell-O, pineapple and water gently for 10 minutes.
Add yogurt and cool.
Add celery and carrots.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill for 6 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: meninite dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine like pie crust.
Add nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 1/2 hour.
Brown meat with onions, liquid smoke and bell pepper.
Drain excess grease.

Add hot links, crushed pepper, 3 strips bacon, crushed pineapple and brown sugar together with meat, onion and liquid smoke in baking dish. Place remaining strips of bacon on top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add small package of jello, flavor of your choice. Mix well and let stand for 1 hour.
Put in jam jars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil medium size pods okra until soft.
Drain water off. Flatten on a paper towel with a fork.
Then meal it well on both sides.
Fry in Crisco until golden brown.
It is delicious with fresh black-eyed peas, fresh tomatoes, homemade cornbread and ice tea.

title: apple crumble
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Line bottom of pan with thinly sliced apples.
Cover with crumble.
Bake at 350° until brown and apples are cooked.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, soup, cheese, 1/3 cup butter, milk, onion, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss cornflakes with 1/4 cup butter in bowl. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 15 servings.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients, add milk and mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls and place on waxed paper lined baking sheet.
Flatten with a glass to 1/4 inches; cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
In a double broiler or microwave safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip patties and place on waxed paper to harden.

title: rice and vegetables
directions: In a deep large skillet, saute onions, green peppers and bouillon cubes.
Add rest of the ingredients except the rice.
Cook on medium heat until everything has been thoroughly cooked.
Add rice; cook on low until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.

If mixture gets too dry while cooking, add more tomato soup or water. Can be served with any type of meat or meat can be cut up into small pieces and added to the mixture after the meat has been thoroughly cooked.
Delicious with pork chops.

title: beef dinner
directions: Wrap all ingredients in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Prepare one recipe for each serving needed.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all together and cook until the celery feels done.
Add thickening (cornstarch with water, kind of thin) until it's as thick as you want it.

title: strawberry nabisco torte
directions: Crunch wafers; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut strawberries in quarters and sweeten slightly.
Chop nuts.
Cream butter, egg yolks and sugar well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread butter and egg mixture on crumbs.
Sprinkle with nuts and berries.
Cover with whipped cream; top with remaining crumbs.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems and chop stems.
Place caps in shallow greased casserole.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon pieces; drain and chop fine.
Saute mushroom stems and onions until onions are tender.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with stems and onions.
Spoon into caps.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Will serve 6.

title: microwave easy oriental carrots and snow peas
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe dish, microwave oil and garlic, uncovered, on High 1 minute or until soft.
Add carrots and snow peas and cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Drain excess water.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, salt, celery seed, green pepper and onion in mixing bowl.

title: alice's lemon cheese
directions: Combine melted butter and sugar in top of double boiler.
Add juice and grated rind.
Beat in eggs and cook over hot but not boiling water until thick.
Stir constantly.
Chill in jelly jar or similar container.
Keep refrigerated.
Spread on toast, English muffins, etc.

title: freezing slaw
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar together; bring to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt.
Add celery seed or anise or both to taste. Let cool.
Pour over cabbage.
Let stand several hours before freezing.

title: navajo reservation macaroni and cheese(modern)
directions: Cook up 3 cups macaroni in pan.
Mix 4 cups milk from the powder and heat.
Add about 2 1/2 cups of cheese and stir until it melts.
Mix in some flour with a little water to make paste. Thicken cheese mixture with paste and add drained, cooked macaroni.
Salt.
Pour in a dish and bake in oven until it firms up.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Juice and grate rind of 1 lemon.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add butter to warm milk, then pour heated milk over beaten yolks slowly, mixing thoroughly.
Add sugar, flour and salt, which have been mixed together, and stir in rind and juice of lemon.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold lightly into mixture.
Pour into buttered custard cups, 2/3 full and bake in pan of hot water 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Combine
zucchini, mushrooms, onions, garlic and butter in
a 2-quart microwave-proof casserole dish.
Cover and cook on
High (maximum power) 8 to 10 minutes, or until vegetables are
tender. Stir
in
tomato paste, 1/3 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook on 70 (Roast) 3
to
1/2 minutes,
or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread, ham and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Mix in medium mixing bowl.
Combine the melted margarine and brown sugar.
Stir in Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Place 3/4 of this in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften ice cream; smooth out and sprinkle remaining over top.
Top with strawberries and Danish dessert.
Serve immediately.
Freeze any leftovers.

title: one pot braised chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in hot oil and butter until golden.
Add onion, potatoes, celery, salt, thyme, pepper, bay leaf and broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until chicken and potatoes are almost tender. Add beans; cover and cook about 10 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: illinois corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Wash leeks well.
Chop all of the white portion and some of the green.
Peel and chop the potatoes.
Combine all in a soup pot with the spices.
Add enough water to cover all by about 1/2 inch. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover and cook for at least 40 minutes.
Let cool somewhat and puree in a blender or mash with a potato masher.
Adjust salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Rinse in cold water.
Mix other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2, 8x4 loaf pans. In large bowl, combine flour, nuts, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and baking powder. Set aside. In large bowl beat at high speed, eggs till frothy. Beat in oil, sugar and vanilla until mixture is thick and foamy. Add to flour mixture. Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Pour into pans. Bake 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes, then on racks.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Then add flour mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.
When done, cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: nephew charley's homemade granola
directions: Dump oats into a 13 x 18 x 1/2-inch cookie sheet with sides. Sprinkle the brown sugar and oil top.
Mix thoroughly with a large spoon.
Smooth mixture to a uniform depth and bake it for 30 minutes at 300°.
Set it aside to cool.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients on top, then spoon into an airtight storage container.

title: artichoke and green beans romano
directions: In large skillet, saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Blend well to absorb oil.
Add beans, artichoke hearts and cheese.
Heat slowly to melt cheese.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chips and butter in large bowl in microwave.
Add Crispix and blend until completely coated.
Shake coated cereal in a large bag of powdered sugar.
Chill in refrigerator.
Yum!

title: crispy quesadillas
directions: For each quesadilla, lightly spread a tortilla with margarine. Sprinkle with the Cheddar and Jack cheeses and top with peppers (use as many as desired).
Fold tortilla in half and spread lightly with margarine.
Cook in frying pan until crispy on both sides.

title: lasagne squares(meatless)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until golden, stirring often. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, oregano and bay leaf. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.

Combine spinach, Ricotta, egg, 1/4 cup Parmesan, salt and pepper. Spoon 1/3 of the tomato sauce in bottom of lasagne dish or 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover with 1/3 lasagne noodles, 1/2 spinach-Ricotta filling, 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Repeat layers, using 1/2 remaining sauce and noodles and all remaining filling. Top with remaining noodles, sauce, Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting into squares for serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut crunchies(croccanti)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and peanuts in large bowl.
Add melted shortening and extract.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff. Add small amount of water to moisten dough to hold together.
(If too soft, add a little more flour.)
Cut or spoon about 1 1/2 inches long and 1/2 inch wide.
Place on greased pans about one inch apart.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes. Take off pan while hot.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 320°.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: tangy cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let flavors blend for a day or so before serving.
Leftover sauce may be stored in refrigerator.

title: chicken breast strips
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut each fillet into 4 long strips.
Combine with eggs in bowl.
Chill overnight.
Roll in crumbs, coating well.
Brown in oil in large skillet.
Alternate layers of chicken, mushrooms and garlic in 9 x 13-inch baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Pour mixture of wine and broth over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients together saving 1/2 can tomato soup to pour over top of meat loaf.
Place in a baking pan.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash until there are no lumps.
Add Neufchatel cheese, sour cream, onion powder, salt, pepper and egg whites; blend well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole that has been sprayed with non-stick vegetable spray.
Dot with margarine.
If preparing ahead, allow to cool, cover and refrigerate for several days, if desired.
To serve, bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes. Makes 12 one cup servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix ingredients lightly.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: individual berry pandowdies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, toss berries with 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk and butter; mix until well combined.
Prepare six 8-ounce custard cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Divide berry mixture among the custard cups.
Top each cup with batter.
Sprinkle each with sugar and nutmeg.
Place cups on baking sheet; bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until tops are golden.
Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: mable's broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° and cool completely.

title: hot fruit side dish
directions: Place all fruit, except cherries, in baking dish.
Boil together for about 10 minutes in double boiler, until thick as cream, the butter, sugar, flour and sherry.
Pour sauce over fruit; garnish with cherries.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: herbed pork loin
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Trim excess fat from roast.
Place split sections of roast on top of each other. Rub surface of roast with herb mixture.
Tie roast at 2 to 3-inch intervals with string.
Place roast in a large browning bag. Prepare according to package directions.

title: meat croquettes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Shape into cones. Roll in flour, then dip in mixture of egg and water, then in fine bread crumbs. Fry in hot oil until a little brown, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Drain on paper. Serve with gravy.

title: french potato au gratin
directions: Peel and slice potatoes round and thin.
Lightly grease casserole dish.
Layer potatoes in dish, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Press garlic over mixture.
Add cream and milk.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are soft and creamy.

title: date-nut-chocolate chip cake
directions: Put dates and soda in bowl; pour boiling water over and let cool. Cream oleo, sugar and eggs. Add flour, salt and soda; mix. Add the date mixture slowly, mixing well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the nuts, sugar and chocolate chips. Sprinkle over top of pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut-date chipperoos
directions: In large bowl, stir all ingredients, except potato chips, until well mixed with hands.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls in crushed potato chips.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes about 36 pieces or 1 1/2 pounds.

title: pancakes made with club soda
directions: Mix well; pour onto a hot
griddle for pancakes or into your waffle iron for delicious waffles.

title: brown bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add raisins, molasses and sweet milk.
Stir well and fill a 16 ounce can 3/4 full.
Cover and steam for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and mix together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Place the soup, water, chopped onion and green chilies in a saucepan.
Stir mixture and cook until hot.
Dip 1 tortilla at a time into hot mixture and then place in bottom of a 9 x 11-inch pan (place a total of 4 in bottom of pan).
Top with some of the soup mixture and grated cheese.
Continue layering until tortillas and soup mixture are gone.
Add more grated cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and cream. Add vanilla. Add flour and mix.
Cover and chill overnight. Roll out and cut cookies.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: devil's food drop cakes
directions: Let shortening melt in hot water before adding other ingredients.
Don't mix until last item has been added.
Then mix well.
If Spry or Crisco is used, add 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cakes.

title: chili
directions: Lightly brown the hamburg and onion.
Add the tomato soup, water and chili powder.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain kidney beans and add to boiling mixture.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: * Add small amounts until smoother.

title: ranch stew
directions: Brown and drain the first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the first mixture and simmer in crock-pot on low heat.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add cake flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Place in greased and waxed tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Serve.

title: fish-lemon-orange roughy
directions: Finely shred the carrot.
In mixing bowl, combine the couscous, onion salt, lemon pepper and nutmeg with shredded carrot.
Add water; stir.
Spray 4 baking (individual) dishes with nonstick spray.
Divide mixture into dishes.
Cut fish into 4 portions. Place fish on top.
Cut lemon half into 4 slices, placing a piece atop each dish.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate for 3 to 24 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix eggs, margarine and sugar until creamy.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas and put over cream mixture. Put crushed pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic together; drain grease, then add corn, tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or potatoes begin to brown.

title: mushroom muenster chicken
directions: Cut boneless chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Pour two beaten eggs over chicken.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator or at least 3 to 4 hours.
Dip chicken in seasoned bread crumbs and brown in a pan.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sliced mushrooms and top with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Coat all sides of meat with flour. In a Dutch oven, brown meat slowly in 2 tablespoons cooking oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add beef broth, basil or thyme and Worcestershire.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and onion soup mix.
(If need to add more liquid, mix soup mix in needed amount of water, beef broth or red wine.) Continue baking, covered, about 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Prepare Pot Roast Gravy.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned spiced pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Beat in eggs. Stir in pumpkin and cream.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Decorate top as desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Chop all vegetables; put together in a bowl.
Add pickles and bacon to vegetables.
Take 1/2 of cornbread and break into bite size pieces in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of vegetables over the cornbread.
Mix 1/4 cup of sweet pickle juice and a cup of mayonnaise together.
Pour 1/2 of this over the vegetables and cornbread.
Repeat the layers again.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; roll cubed beef into mixture. Shake off excess.
Melt shortening over high heat in a Dutch oven or a heavy-bottomed pot with cover.
When shortening is hot, add cubed beef (4 or 5 pieces at a time, so as not to crowd them). Brown beef on all sides and remove, then add additional pieces.

title: flounder kiev
directions: Combine butter, parsley, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and garlic.
Place butter mixture on waxed paper and form into a roll.
Chill until hard.
Skin fillets and divide into strips about 6 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Place a piece of butter at one end of each strip of fish.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Roll fish in flour; dip in beaten eggs to which water has been added; roll in crumbs.
Chill for at least 1 hour. Fry in deep fat for 2 or 3 minutes, or until brown and fish is flaky.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6.

title: cookies and cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreos or put in blender.
Use about 3/4 of the package. Let ice cream soften, so you can spread.
Layer in glass 9 x 12-inch dish:
crushed Oreos, ice cream, fudge topping and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with crushed Oreos.
Leave in freezer at least 2 hours before serving.

title: country pie(main meal)
directions: Crust:
Mix together 1/2 cup tomato sauce, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, meat, onions, green peppers, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper and oregano.
Pat into a 9-inch pie plate, side and bottom.

title: pam's party potatoes
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese until blended.
Add hot potatoes gradually, whipping constantly, until light and fluffy. Season with onion and garlic salt.
Spoon into 2-quart ungreased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and brown in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes, until warm.

title: fresh fruit medley
directions: Divide fruit among 6 dessert dishes.
Just before serving, spoon 2 tablespoons fruit concentrate onto each.
Makes 1 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour into large mixing bowl.
Measure out 2 cups flour and place back in bowl.
Add sugars, salt and Crisco.
Stir lightly.
Break all eggs into separate bowl, add vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs to flour and beat until smooth.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Use Bundt pan that has been greased with solid Crisco.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In a 2-quart large baking dish, layer coarsely chopped chicken. Mix soup and sour cream and sherry to season to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs and poppy seeds.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice in pressure cooker with a half tablespoon of bacon drippings.
Add enough water to form a thin gravy (so the beans have adequate liquid to expand) and cook at pressure 15 for 25 minutes.
The flavor gets better if it can sit for a while before serving (and is even better the next day). Serve over steaming rice with corn relish or chow-chow for a genuine Cajun experience!

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil and mash squash.
Add butter, salt, pepper, eggs (beaten), sugar, milk and crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy supper skillet
directions: Brown beef
in
skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix, rice and water.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tofu sauteed
directions: Remove the tofu from water.
Wrap the tofu in paper towels for at least 20 minutes to remove as much moisture as possible.
Wrap the tofu in fresh paper towels; press between the palms of your hands to remove any remaining water.
Sprinkle each side of the tofu cake with minced garlic or onion salt.
With a small, sharp knife, slit one side of each tofu cake to create a pocket. Sprinkle the pocket with a little flour and insert approximately 1 ounce of cheese in each tofu cake.
Sprinkle the outside of each tofu cake with flour.
Beat the egg in a medium size bowl.
Add the sesame seed or bread crumbs.
Dip each tofu cake into the egg batter; fry in a small amount of oil until brown on each side. Serve the tofu with a sauce of one part soy sauce and one part mayonnaise (or mayonnaise and ketchup).

title: dried beef cheese ball(club member: renee evans)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat the eggs with milk; add 1 tablespoon melted Crisco and corn.
Combine the 2 mixtures lightly.
Drop from a teaspoon into deep fat, heated to 365°.
Fry until brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, then add the Cool Whip.

title: seafood salad sandwiches
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients well and chill. Serve as a sandwich, salad or chunky dip.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs and water.
Mix thoroughly.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Use 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cut twinkies in half (lengthwise). Place in pan cream side up.
Take can of Eagle Brand milk and pour over cake.
Pour crushed pineapple (with juice) and pour over cake. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut up vegetables, place in large jar or covered container. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Marinate overnight.

title: popcorn
directions: Put optional amount of popcorn kernels in popcorn popper.
Plug popper into outlet.
Wait till all kernels are popped into bowl. Then heat butter on stove or in microwave until melted.
Then pour onto popcorn and pour optional amount of salt on.

title: hot fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples in pot with all ingredients except prepared pie crust until soft. Roll prepared dough out the size of 7-inch round plate. Fill one side of dough with apples. Close ends of dough with fork, both sides together. Drop little pockets of apple pies in hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: deviled dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Cover and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yields 1 cup.
Contains only 11 calories.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package and pour into a 10 x 15-inch or larger pan.
While cake is warm, poke holes in cake (with wooden spoon handle).
Pour 2 cans Eagle Brand milk over cake, then pour Mrs. Richardson's caramel butterscotch topping over cake.
(Usually found over frozen foods freezers or with chocolate syrups.
It is in a glass jar.)
Cool.

title: nana's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in boiling water with salt and curry powder.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Do not overcook. Drain.
Dry potatoes by shaking pan over low heat.
Put the potatoes in a bowl with a mixture of the next 7 ingredients.
Set in refrigerator to marinate 1 to 2 hours, turning several times. Meanwhile, prepare eggs, celery and green pepper.
Add eggs and vegetables to potatoes with mayonnaise.
Toss lightly to coat all ingredients evenly.
Set in refrigerator to chill thoroughly before serving.
Yield:
about 6 servings.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of 11 x 7 x 1-inch baking pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in brown sugar, nuts and coconut.
Spread evenly on top of pressed dough.
Bake at 350°. Remove while still a little soft to the touch, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except frozen strawberries).
Then add frozen strawberries.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients in baking pan.
Add milk and mix well. Melt butter and pour over batter.
Add fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and cheddar cheese quiche
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain well.
Combine mushrooms, basil, salt, green pepper, parsley and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon into cooled pie shell; top with cheese.
Combine milk and eggs, beating just until frothy.
Pour evenly over cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned and quiche is set.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine saltines and 4 tablespoons of butter, then press into 9-inch pie plate.
Saute remaining butter with onions, place in pie shell.
Combine eggs, sour cream, Ricotta, dill, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Pour over onions, sprinkle with cheese and garnish with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken swiss bake
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices. Mix soup with water.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: drum stick torte
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix wafers, peanuts and butter.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour and extract.
Spread 3/4 of dough on 16 inch cookie sheet, greased.
Spread on cherry pie filling.
Drop the rest of dough on by spoonful.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add flour, chips and pecans.
Mix. Form dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are golden.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: punch (pink)
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
At last minute, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Serves 16.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Beat mashed bananas, eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla in bowl until well blended.
In another large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Make well in center of dry ingredients and pour in the banana mixture.
Mix until blended.
Scoop into muffin cups.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes a dozen muffins.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together then pour into a buttered 3 quart casserole. Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: parmesan puffs
directions: Heat broiler. In small bowl combine mayonnaise, onion & cheese. Divide mixture evenly over bread slices. Place on broiler pan and broil until golden and bubbly, about 30-45 seconds. Garnish with scallions if desired. Serve warm.

title: chicken adobo
directions: If you like, remove skin from chicken.
Rub pepper into chicken.
Place in a non-aluminum pot.
Mix vinegar and soy sauce together and pour over chicken.
Mix a second batch of vinegar and soy sauce and pour over chicken.
Pour the water over the chicken. (If the chicken is not covered, add just enough water to cover.) Add bay leaves and other spices, if desired.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: holiday crackers
directions: Pour oil and seasonings over crackers and mix well. Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°. Stir after 5 minutes. Pour crackers out on brown paper bag lined with paper towels to cool.

title: new year's eve dip
directions: In large frying pan or saucepan, saute onion in butter until soft.
Add cheese and black-eyed peas, stirring until cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Serve in chafing dish with chips.
May be prepared ahead.
Serves 10.

title: christmas fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all chopped ingredients into dry mixture.
Add eggs, sherry and milk to butter and sugar mixture.
Using hands in large bowl, combine the fruit mixture with the liquid mixture. Drop cookies onto buttered cookie sheet with spoon and bake until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes at 275°.
Makes 12 dozen or more.

title: gramma's beef swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces. Mix flour, salt and pepper. Pound mixture into meat.
Brown steak slowly on all sides in a little oil in large skillet.
Don't rush this browning step. Remove steak to roasting pan.
Add onions to grease and cook until clear in color.
Put cooked onions on top of meat.
Add gravy. Cover and cook at 350° for 2 hours.
(Slow cooking is the key to its goodness.) Serves 5 to 6.

title: german fondue sauce
directions: Melt butter; add mustard and seasonings. Stir well and carefully add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Slowly add lemon juice being careful not to let mixture curdle. Beat well and return to heat. Stir constantly over medium heat until sauce begins to thicken.

title: the kings wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well with yeast.
Knead well.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Punch down and divide into 4 portions.
Place dough into 4 oiled loaf pans.
Let rise 3/4 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: crab lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, adding olive oil to boiling water.
Rinse and drain.
Combine shrimp soup, crab, cottage cheese, cream cheese (softened), onion, egg, salt and basil.
Layer 1/2 of the noodles in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread with 1/2 the crab mixture; sprinkle with 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Top with remaining noodles, crab and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh fruit ambrosia
directions: In bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chuck wagon bean salad
directions: Prepare pasta or elbow macaroni according to the package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Drain 4-bean salad, reserving 1 tablespoon of the liquid.
In a medium mixing bowl, toss together pasta and drained salad.
Stir together reserved liquid and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Add to pasta mixture.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter casserole dish, set aside. In a medium bowl, mix together butter, sugar, flour and oats. Place half the apples in prepared casserole dish. Sprinkle with half the crumbs. Repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Add water and soda to raisins and dates in bowl; let cool. In second bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended. Stir in flour alternately with cooled fruit mixture just until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Wrap airtight and store overnight before serving.
Yields 2 loaves, about 18 thin slices each.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Slightly beat 2 eggs and set aside. When margarine is melted, add corn with liquid, sour cream, and sugar. Stir and add eggs. Add corn muffin mix. Stir well. Pour into a 1 3/4 quart casserole dish that is coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients, except beaten egg whites.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jello fluff yum!
directions: Prepare jello with 3 3/4 cups hot water and refrigerate until firm.
In mixer, put chilled jello and softened cream cheese; mix at high speed until fluffy.
Remove from mixer and add the fruit. Fold in Cool Whip; chill.
Yum!

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Mix sugar and melted margarine.
Beat egg slightly, then combine all ingredients.
Place in refrigerator in large bowl (about 4 times larger than mixture).
Cover tightly. Dough is best when thoroughly cold or made the night before.

title: new england sweet cider punch
directions: Extract juices from oranges and lemon; add to cider together with cherries.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: pickle beets
directions: Pour over beets and let simmer 15 minutes.
Not quite enough vinegar for 4 quarts 3 times the amount is enough for 10 quarts.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Let Cheddar cheese and cream cheese stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Combine salad dressing mix, mayonnaise and milk in mixer bowl; mix well.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Chill, covered, in freezer for 30 minutes.
Shape into ball; coat with almonds.
Fat 16 grams total.

title: vegetarian vegetable soup
directions: Cook onion, green pepper, cabbage, corn, carrots and celery until partially tender in about 3 cups water or in just enough to cover.
Simmer about 15 minutes or longer.
Add potatoes; cook about 15 minutes.
Add spice, salt, sugar, black pepper, beans, V-8 juice and can of tomatoes plus about 2 1/2 cans water.
Simmer on low heat for about 1 1/2 hours, then add macaroni and peas; cook about 45 minutes, or until macaroni is just tender.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet over medium heat until crisp. Add green onions, red pepper and peas;
stir-fry 1 minute. Add egg and scramble. Stir in rice and cook until heated, gently separating grains. Add soy sauce. Cook, stirring until heated through. Serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: In skillet or wok, in 2 tablespoons oil, stir-fry chicken strips until opaque.
Remove and set aside.

title: tropical punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid as per package in punch bowl.
Add can of pineapple juice and 2 liters ginger ale.
Stir, add ice and serve chilled.
May add additional sugar, if not sweet enough.

title: aunt martha's chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix together with a spoon, not an electric mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan and bake at 350` for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: skid road stroganoff
directions: Start cooking those noodles, first dropping a bouillon cube into water.
Brown the garlic onions and crumbled beef in the oil. Add the paprika, salt, flour and mushrooms.
Stir and let it cook five minutes, then add the soup and simmer ten minutes.
Stir in sour cream, keeping the heat low so not to curdle the sour cream and let heat through.
To serve, put noodles on a platter, put on stroganoff mix.
Add parsley and serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain the canned vegetables.
Add the green pepper, celery and onion to taste.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and water; bring to a boil.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add sugar.
Then add dark syrup.
Next add pecans.
Then add melted butter and vanilla.
Real butter gives so much more flavor.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell. Bake about 1 hour or until center is set, when a knife comes out clean at 350°.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Peel and grate carrots; add the other ingredients and mix well.
Serves six 1/2-cup servings.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 425° to 450°.
Melt oleo in bottom of baking dish.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste; roll in flour.
Place in baking dish and cook in oven, uncovered, turning chicken so that it will begin to brown on both sides.
Remove from oven and turn oven to 350°.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Cover and return to oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: long anise cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until dough is smooth. Make long rolls and place on greased cookie sheets. Place only 3 rolls per sheet because dough will spread.
Before baking, brush beaten egg yolk over top and sides of rolls. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still warm, cut into thin, slanted slices.

title: sausage squares
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Brown sausage and onions; drain. Spread over dough. Mix egg, cheese, chilies and remaining mayonnaise and spread over sausage. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: blueberry treat
directions: Soften butter or oleo.
Drain blueberries, if canned.
In large mixer bowl, combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder, salt, butter, milk and eggs.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange blueberries on top. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cut into squares and serve warm or cool, with whipped or ice cream.

title: raspberry almond thumbprints cookies
directions: Note:
Chill dough for 1 hour to prevent dough from spreading.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so as to not lose the boil.
Keep at rolling boil until peanuts pop and liquid turns caramel color. Remove from heat.
Add soda and salt.
Stir well.
Pour on well-greased cookie sheet that has been lightly buttered and sprinkled with salt.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Stir well and bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir in milk, simmer, stirring constantly until mixture comes to soft ball stage (234° to 238°). Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn (air popped works best). Stir to cool.
Butter hands lightly.
Shape into balls about 3 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: sauteed cabbage with bacon and bread crumbs
directions: Cook bacon in a heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring, until crisp and transfer with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
In remaining drippings in skillet, cook cabbage, water, salt and pepper to taste until crisp-tender and transfer to a serving dish.
In skillet, heat reserved drippings over moderately high heat.
Saute bread crumbs and caraway seed.
Stir in bacon and sprinkle over cabbage.

title: mama's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into small blocks.
In a pan, place cheese and Ro-Tel on a low flame.
Once cheese has melted, add peppers; cook for 2 minutes.
Serve with your favorite chips or meat and vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend cooked chicken, cream of celery soup, carrots and celery and place in flat baking dish.
Top with stuffing, hot water and butter mixture after mixing together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour half the batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; add chocolate syrup to remaining batter and swirl in. Pour remaining mixture over top of the other batter.
Bake 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
May take a little longer to bake.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 Tbsp. milk and 1 Tbsp. sugar in bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Fold in 1
1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Blend 1 cup milk and vanilla pudding.
Add pumpkin, cinnamon, ginger, and cloves.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: boston baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients except bacon.
Cut bacon into pieces and arrange on casserole.
Bake uncovered about 45 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and bacon is crisp.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; take stems out. Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Saute stems separately.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff mushrooms.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: potatoes for a crowd
directions: Mix defrosted potatoes with 1 stick melted margarine or butter and set aside.

title: brandy pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Blend dry ingredients together.
Mix extracts and brandy together.
Mix flour into sugar mixture with extracts and sour cream.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add your lard or oil.
Slowly add the warm water and mix into a soft dough.
If the dough is too soft, add more flour.
Form into small balls and roll out.
Cook on hot griddle for about a minute on each side.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mimi's apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: curried red lentil soup
directions: Rinse and clean lentils under cold running water.
Put in a medium-sized saucepan along with water, oil and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes, over medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add diced potatoes.

title: chili
directions: Saute together meat, onions, celery and green pepper until meat is no longer pink; drain fat.
In a large kettle, combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer on low heat for two hours.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Remove skin; wash and cut off fat.
Soak an hour in salt and vinegar water (about 2 tablespoons of vinegar).
Beat eggs lightly.
Salt and pepper legs.
Dip in flour, then in eggs.
Dip again in flour.
Fry in deep oil until done on medium-high heat. Turn down and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Make jello by directions on box.
When partly set, add sour cream, nuts and celery.
Fold carefully and chill.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cream Crisco and eggs until fluffy, then gradually add sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Slowly add enough milk to make it so you can spread it on the cake.
Beat all this very good.
You can make this chocolate and store in a plastic bowl with a tight lid for several days.
Take out few hours ahead to get soft.

title: aunt clara mae's foolproof cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in oven in an 8-inch square casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour on top of melted butter.
Don't stir.
Top with fruit.
Don't stir.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon de lush
directions: CRUST:
Melt butter and mix with flour and pecans. Press out in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Chill while making filling.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Add to frying pan the last 5 minutes the green pepper and onion.
Drain grease from bacon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: merry cranberry bread
directions: One bowl method:
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes; let stand 10 minutes; remove.

title: erma's chicken wings
directions: Step 1:
Using kitchen shears, cut each wing into 2 pieces. In a large deep skillet, heat the oil over moderate heat.
Fry the wings for about 5 minutes or until done.
Transfer to paper towels.
